title: Head of Group Technology Platforms
description: NEW SENIOR LEADERSHIP ROLE tasked with developing and executing our strategy to integrate and modernise Technology Platforms across the Group.
jobType: The Group Technology Division  Our Technology Division is about to embark on an operational uplift, driving modernisation and adopting leading technologies to stay at the forefront of digital and innovation. Every day brings new challenges and opportunities, our Technology leaders are committed to creating a work environment where everyone can make a meaningful contribution and excel.  We are thrilled to be seeking a Head of Group Technology Platformsto join the senior technology leadership team reporting to the Group CIO.  The Position  The Head of Group Technology Platforms has overall accountability for the Groups technology platforms, developing and driving the strategy and framework to integrate and modernise platforms, while ensuring alignment with our multi-brand strategy. The position will work collaboratively with peer technology teams as well as other business units to create a unified and scalable ecosystem.  This is a key leadership role responsible for leading and upskilling team capability so that the Groups technology platform offers best-in-class security, resilience and reliability. As a technology change agent, this position will offer the unique challenges and opportunities that come with driving technological transformation.  What will your key responsibilities include?  Design and execute the technology platform strategy and roadmap, aligned with business objectives. Lead the transformation of legacy systems through integration and modernisation, driving efficiency, innovation and cost effectiveness. Meet future business demands by driving growth and scalability of our platform capabilities. Inform the development of the overall solutions architecture to ensure platforms are designed and engineered to facilitate and empower innovative product development and promote automation, reuse, and consistency across the technology ecosystem. Lead and empower a high performing team to deliver, integrate and modernise Platform delivery. Champion collaboration and alignment among NGM Technology Teams, NGM Group Business units, and external partners during Technology projects. Bring diversity of thought and experience that will drive our organisation forward, while also sharing our organisational values.  What are we looking for?  At least 15 years experience as a senior platform leader within a financial services environment. Proven experience developing and executing a platform strategy and roadmap. Demonstrable experience successfully driving a platform integration and modernisation program across a financial services organisation. A technology change agent who can champion change initiatives and influence others to engage in change and navigate from current state to future desired state. Demonstrated experience reporting to or interacting directly with the executive committee. Formal qualification in Business, Commerce, IT or relevant discipline.  What can you expect from us?  NGM Group employees can take advantage of the following work perks:  Health and wellbeing; Fitness passport, corporate health insurance and annual flu vaccination. Lifestyle and giving back; Flexible work including hybrid arrangements, hotel discounts, 14 weeks paid parental leave, two community volunteer days per year and three recreational leave days per year. Professional advancement; Diverse career opportunities, recognition programs and employee referral program.  About us  Were NGM Group, and we offer retail banking services to more than half a million Australians under the brands Greater Bank and Newcastle Permanent. We have fresh energy and big goals for our customers, and our people are key to us achieving this success. If youre ready to be part of a team that puts the customer first and enjoys a challenge as the path to growth and innovation, then  we want you!  NGM Group is committed to delivering trusted banking to enable our customers and communities to thrive. We do this by leading with heart, doing the right things in the right way, and by maintaining high standards of ethical behaviour in everything that we do. All applicants are therefore required to undergo a skills assessment, comprehensive background check, Bankruptcy Check and a National Police Check.  We are also working to reflect the vibrant communities we serve. We believe in creating an inclusive, diverse, and supportive workplace where everyone can thrive. If you require adjustments to be made during the recruitment process or would like to discuss any accessibility requirements, your Talent Acquisition Partner will be happy to engage in a confidential discussion and assist. Your unique talents and perspectives are what make us stronger.

title: Head of Group Technology Enterprise Services
description: NEW SENIOR LEADERSHIP ROLE tasked with executing the strategic direction of our Digital Workplace, Service Management & Technical Services functions.
jobType: The Group Technology Division  Our Technology Division is about to embark on an operational uplift, driving modernisation and adopting leading technologies to stay at the forefront of digital and innovation. Every day brings new challenges and opportunities, our Technology leaders are committed to creating a work environment where everyone can make a meaningful contribution and excel.  We are thrilled to be seeking a Head of Group Technology Enterprise Servicesto join the senior technology leadership team reporting to the Group CIO.  The Position  The Head of Group Technology Enterprise Services, has overall accountability for the Groups Digital Workplace Technology, Service Management and all Technology Services deployed on behalf of NGM Group. In this position, you will design and execute the strategic direction of the Enterprise Services team, driving initiatives to modernise our technological infrastructure and networks, transitioning to a cloud first environment and foster a digitally empowered workplace.  You will apply your exceptional leadership skills to drive a diverse, multi-disciplinary team to ensure all technology services are efficient, secure and perform optimally.  What will your key responsibilities include?  Design and execute the technology Enterprise Services group strategy and roadmap, aligned with business objectives. Lead the integration and modernisation of Digital Workplace Technologies, Service Management, Infrastructure and Network services including integration and consolidation of On Premise and Cloud environments aimed at enhancing efficiency, scalability and cost effectiveness. Act as a Technology change agent, support senior stakeholder engagement related to implementations, upgrades, or optimisations and broader operating model. title: Business Systems Support Officer
description: This position will effectively contribute to the development, maintenance, and support of Councils Business Systems.
jobType: About the Business  South Burnett Regional Council is one of the largest employers within the region, with offices and depots located in Kingaroy, Nanango, Wondai, Murgon, Proston and Blackbutt.  Council recognises our key role we play within the community and the services we provide to our ratepayers & public members. We understand our duty to provide excellent customer service at the forefront of all our processes and services, to all stakeholders.  Council is comprised of four (4) Departments: Executive Services, Liveability, Finance & Corporate, and Infrastructure. These Departments consist of multiple branches to ensure we provide efficient services and accurate information to our community. We believe our staff are our greatest asset in achieving objectives. With approximately 330 employees, Council takes a proactive approach towards recruitment and retention of high-calibre employees.  Further our commitment to our staff we pride ourselves on developing our staff members through our learning and development policy and procedure. Annual Employee Development Reviews are undertaken to ensure our staff are continuously developing.  Council is committed to providing a workplace that is safe and without risk to the health and safety of all employees, contractors, volunteers, work-experience students, visitors, and members of the public. We have a adopted a Zero Harm Strategy to promote safety within the organisation. We recognise the importance of developing and maintaining healthy and safe working conditions in all workplaces and the importance of keeping the work health and safety practices in these workplaces under constant review.  South Burnet Regional Council are committed to establishing a harmonious and sustainable workforce. This is achieved by adhering to equitable recruitment practices and equal opportunity regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, disability, or sexual orientation.  About the Region  The South BurnettRegion is ideally situated just 2 - 3 hours' drive to Brisbane, Toowoomba, Sunshine Coast and Fraser Coast. The region is home to the stunning Bunya Mountains, where you can enjoy spectacular rainforest walks, nights by the fire in hidden chalets and the best scenic views Queensland has to offer. The South Burnett region is renowned for its great wine, gourmet foods and recreational facilities such as Lake Boondooma and Yallakool tourist parks.  About the role  Based in Kingaroy Maximum Term (up to 17 Months) - Full Time $71K - $82K per annum + Allowances + Super  Council is seeking an officer to effectively contribute to the development, maintenance and support of Council's Business Systems through the provision of specialist advice, analysis, and support within Council. This role will provide helpdesk support, configure system modules, and create appropriate reporting capabilities to reflect business requirements. This position will also provide service to ensure the development and maintenance of good working relationships with all staff, and all key stakeholders. The successful applicant will have a sound understanding and demonstrated experience in the management of Local Government Business Systems (specifically the TechnologyOne Suite), ability to provide effective helpdesk support, hold experience in development and delivery of end user training, as well as ability to problem solve, manage time and exercise good judgment/ initiative.  Mandatory Qualifications  Minimum requirement of a current C Class drivers licence  Desirable Qualifications  Certificate IV Information Technology, Business or Project Management (or significant proven experience in a relevant field)  Benefits and perks  Work/Life balance (9 Day Fortnight Roster) Up to 12% employer superannuation contribution Access to Salary Packaging Benefits Access to Corporate memberships Access to Health and Wellbeing programs  Skills and experience  **Please address the following key selection criteria items below, as part of your application**  Sound understanding and demonstrated experience in the management of Local Government Business Systems, specifically the TechnologyOne suite, and an ability to adapt as systems are upgraded, redeveloped, or integrated. Demonstrated ability to effectively provide helpdesk support to users across all levels of the organisation with variable levels of technical understanding. Proven experience in the development and delivery of effective end user training via a variety of training platforms (i.e., face-to-face, video and skype). Proven experience in the configuration and testing of system changes for the delivery of system implementations, including development of appropriate reporting mechanisms. Sound organisational and project skills with the ability to problem solve, establish work priorities across multiple tasks, meet competing deadlines. Demonstrated ability to exercise sound judgement, initiative, confidentiality, and accuracy in the performance of duties, as well as soft skills including positive attitude, being a team player and focus on continuous improvement and personal development.  Lodging your application  Please make sure your application includes:  A cover letter including statements addressing the key selection criteria. Current resume. Copies of your tickets, licences and qualification that are listed on the position description.  Please note, seek only has the option to provide two attachments, one being your cover letter and the other being your resume. In order to provide key selection criteria and copies of qualifications/ tickets, please include these into your cover letter document/ attachment.  For further information and to review the selection criteria and position description, please visit: https://www.southburnett.qld.gov.au/homepage/98/jobs-and-careers  Applications close 4:00pm Friday, 23 August 2024  Applicants must have the right to live and work in Australia to apply. title: IT Service Management Specialist
description: Play a pivotal role in ensuring Councils adherence to ITIL frameworks and processes.
jobType: Full Time Fixed Term Position - 2 Year Contract  Band 7 - Salary Range $106,626 to $119,182 per annum + 11.5% Super + ADO  Salary offered will depend on level of skills and experience.  About Melton City Council  The City of Melton is a community where everyone belongs. Ours is a vibrant and diverse municipality  one of the fastest developing in Australia. Our organisation strives to provide our community with state-of-the-art amenity and facilities, engaging health and wellbeing options, and support to become active members of our Lifelong Learning City.  We invest in innovation, offering professional and personal development, and generous leave and flexibility to staff, while also fostering a collaborative and inclusive culture. Youll be able to work close to home in a dynamic setting featuring cafes and retail options set amongst heritage buildings and open green spaces.  The Opportunity  At the Melton City Council, we strive to create a vibrant and liveable city accessible to all. The Information Technology department contributes to this vision by transforming Melton City Council service delivery to achieve operational excellence, build community trust and enhance citizen experience when engaging with council services.  As the IT Service Management Specialist, you will play a pivotal role in ensuring Councils adherence to ITIL frameworks and processes. You will be responsible for managing major incidents, changes, and problems to minimise service disruptions, ensure timely IT issue resolution, and enhance overall service delivery.  Key Responsibilities  Coordinate and manage major incidents, ensuring prompt resolution and effective communication with stakeholders. Conduct post-incident reviews to implement corrective actions. Review, assess, and facilitate change requests, ensuring minimal disruption to services. Lead Change Advisory Board (CAB) meetings and monitor change implementations. Identify root causes of recurring incidents and implement strategies to prevent their recurrence. Maintain and track a problem management database. Ensure adherence to the ITIL framework and internal policies and maintain & audit process documentation. Build strong relationships with IT teams, business units, and external vendors through clear communication and collaboration. Identify opportunities for process improvements, implement best practices, and track key performance indicators (KPIs) to enhance IT service delivery. Prepare regular reports on ITIL process performance.  To view the Position Description, click here.  About you   To be successful in this role you will have the following:  Relevant tertiary qualifications with several years of subsequent relevant experience or lesser formal qualifications with extensive relevant experience. Foundation level certificate in ITIL. Proven track record of managing and resolving major incidents, conducting root cause analysis, and implementing effective changes in IT environments. Familiarity with incident and change management tools and platforms. Proficiency in ITIL framework and related processes, including incident management, problem management, and change management. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to analyse data, identify trends, and make data-driven decisions to improve IT service delivery. Leadership qualities to motivate and guide teams during incident response and change implementation.  Culture and Values  Our vision for our community is to be: "A vibrant, safe and liveable city accessible to all" and that means theres a place here for you too. Our organisational values represent us as an established growth Council and the values are reflected in everything we do; our decision-making, our actions and our service provision to the community. Council has a diverse and vibrant organisation and wed love to have you join us to help shape a city for the future.  We are Vibrant MELTON. Our values are:  Motivate Empower Lead Trust Open Nurture  Benefits  There are a number of great reasons why our people love working at Melton City Council:  Staff Benefits | Melton City Council  13 ADO's (Accrued Day Off) per year 5 weeks annual leave Flexible Working Hours Extensive Career Development & Leadership Programs 16 weeks Paid Parental Leave (Super is paid during parental leave) 3 weeks Paid Secondary Carer Leave Family Room available including Breastfeeding Facilities (Melton City Council | Australian Breastfeeding Association) Wellbeing initiatives Subsidised Uniforms  How To Apply  If you require further information about the position, please contact Umair Saleem, IT Workplace Services Lead on 9747 5450.  Applications must include a Resume and address the Key Selection Criteria outlining your suitability to the role. To address the Key Selection Criteria, you will need to write short statements explaining how you meet the criteria, or how you demonstrate the capability. We encourage you to keep your responses concise.  To be eligible for employment at Melton City Council you must be legally entitled to work in Australia.  All successful applicants will need to undertake pre-employment requirements including but not limited to a satisfactory criminal history record check. Successful applicants must be able to comply with any COVID-19 Public Health Orders applicable to Local Government employees.  We strongly encourage job applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disabilities, LGBTIQA+ and people from culturally diverse backgrounds. If selected for an interview and you require any additional support or adjustments regarding interview arrangements, please advise the contact listed above in advance.  Melton City Council is committed to being a child safe organisation and has Zero tolerance for child abuse. Melton City Council is committed to creating and maintaining a child safe organisation where protecting children and preventing and responding to child abuse is at the centre of our everyday thinking and service delivery.  Applications close 11:59pm Wednesday 14 August 2024

Experience or passion to learn Chat GPT and Microsoft Copilot is highly desirable. Experience with MS Dynamics and PowerShell is desirable. Strong communication and teamwork skills. title: Retail Technology Assistant
description: An exciting opportunity exists for a highly skilled and motivated Retail Technology Assistant to work within a vibrant supportive team.
jobType: About Australian United Retailers (AUR)  Australian United Retailers Ltd. (AUR) is a support office for independently owned supermarkets, convenience stores, and liquor retailers. Trading under well-known retail brands such as FoodWorks, Farmer Jacks, and LiquorWorks, we focus on strengthening our retailers' growth and sustainability.    Position Summary  We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Retail Technology Assistant.The Retail Technology Assistant role is diverse role responsible for providing IT support, network assistance and a range of retail-based accountabilities. This role is crucial for the successful onboarding of our stores to our loyalty program, providing support for integration between POS systems and the loyalty provider, and assisting in the day-to-day operations of the loyalty system. In addition to this you will be assisting the wider technology team with interactionsincluding but not limited to telecommunications, broadband, gift cards, daily scan data collection, online shopping, and internal data cleansing.    The ideal candidate will have a strong technical & business background and the ability to translate technical matters into non-technical business processes.    Key Responsibilities  Onboarding Stores: Lead the onboarding process for new stores joining our loyalty program, ensuring a smooth and efficient transition. Integration Support: Provide expert support for the integration of POS systems with our loyalty provider, troubleshooting and resolving any issues that arise. Daily Operations: Assist in the day-to-day operations of the loyalty system, including monitoring performance, addressing any technical issues, and ensuring the system runs smoothly. Road mapping Enhancements: Develop and maintain a roadmap for enhancements to the loyalty system, working closely with stakeholders to prioritize and implement new features. Communication: Translate complex technical concepts into clear, non-technical language for business stakeholders. Ensure excellent communication both spoken and written. Documentation: Write and maintain comprehensive technical and knowledge base documentation to support the loyalty system and its users. Team Collaboration: Work collaboratively with various teams to see the bigger picture and contribute to the overall success of the loyalty program. Autonomous Work: Capable of working independently with minimal supervision while maintaining high standards and meeting deadlines. Business Focus: Maintain a strong focus on business objectives, ensuring that technical solutions align with business needs and goals. Security Focus: Ensure that all aspects of the loyalty program adhere to security best practices and regulatory requirements. Other relevant duties within the team as required.    Required Qualifications  Proven experience in a similar role, specifically in the retail loyalty space. Strong technical aptitude with the ability to learn and adapt to new technologies quickly. Excellent written and spoken English skills. Demonstrated ability to translate technical matters into non-technical business processes. Keen eye for detail and a strong focus on business objectives. Ability to work both independently and collaboratively within a team. Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to think strategically. Knowledge of POS systems and integration processes. Understanding of security best practices and regulatory requirements in the context of loyalty programs. Proficiency in writing technical and knowledge base documentation.    Preferred Qualifications  Experience with specific loyalty program software or providers. Familiarity with project management tools and methodologies. Background in IT or computer science.    Application Process  To apply, please submit your resume and a cover letter detailing your relevant experience and why you are a perfect fit for this role.    AUR conducts knowledge checks as part of the onboarding process.    Equal Opportunity Employer  Australian United Retailers is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.

jobType: Technology Portfolio Lead (Australian Operations)    DISCOVER A BRIGHTER FUTURE  At South32, we're meeting the challenge of enabling a sustainable future through our focus on responsibly producing commodities critical for a low-carbon world. title: IT - 2025 Graduate Program
description: Power your career with Ampol and apply to our 2025 IT program
jobType: Company description:    We are proud of our heritage. We have been powering better journeys for all Australians for over 100 years. As Australia's very own fuel brand, we are committed to making those journeys easier by meeting Australia's needs at every step with the care and service we all deserve. And, as we grow, we continue to evolve, to ensure we have low-carbon solutions that will meet the needs of our customers well into the future.  We are proud to be an endorsed employer of choice for women by WORK180. To understand more about Ampol's policies, benefits and how we support our people, check out some key female leader career stories on the Work180 website.    Job description:   Sydney based program Seeking graduates with degrees in Information Technology, Data Science and Engineering February 2025 commencement date   Power your career with Ampol today!   We've been powering journeys for over 100 years, and we'll be here powering journeys for 100 more. Our culture at Ampol is inclusive, open and team-orientated and we let our employees be themselves while achieving great results!   Join Our Graduate Program:  Are you a highly motivated graduate currently studying Information Technology, Data Science and Engineering? We're inviting two graduates to be part of an excellent 2-year program within our IT division. As an IT Graduate, you'll have the unique opportunity to be part of an exciting phase of growth and transformation at Ampol.   You'll be part of a dynamic team that operates in an agile environment and you'll engage with a diverse stakeholder group of an ASX-listed business.   Hired on a permanent full-time basis, you'll complete 6-month rotations across the respective business units where you will learn and develop under the guidance of our Leaders and teams. Our Leaders bring strong technical expertise, cross-functional experience, and a commercial focus that propels our business forward and they are dedicated to passing on their knowledge to the next generation, which could be you!   Program Details:  Start Date: February 2025 Location: Sydney Based Program - Our brand-new, purpose-built office in Sydney, Alexandria, conveniently close to Green Square Station. Hybrid: This role offers flexibility to work from home   Why Ampol? At Ampol, we're leading the way in the petroleum industry's transformation. Our strategic vision is centred around future energy solutions, creating exciting opportunities for our company, our customers and valued employees.   About you:  To be successful, you will be entering your final year of study in 2024 or completed your undergraduate within the last two years and will be available to commence full-time employment in February 2025. We seek individuals who showcase outstanding analytical and complex problem-solving abilities, strong technical skills like coding and the ability to work in a team environment.   You will have excellent academic results, curious to learn and eager to develop your professional career.   Please note: Ampol will only be considering Australian Citizens and Permanent Residents for our Graduate Program.    Our application process:   We look for success-orientated, agile, and innovative thinkers. We love graduates who take pride in their work and aspire to be part of a high-performance team.  During the application process, you will be asked to provide your top two graduate stream preferences. If you apply to multiple streams, please be aware we will only consider the first two preferences on your initial application. If you change your preferences in subsequent applications outside of your initial application, Ampol will not consider your application.   The recruitment process for our graduates is as follows:   Submit your application  What to include? Personal details, CV, GPA, transcripts, and right-to-work evidence.   Complete a video interview  Shortlisted applicants will be invited to a digital interview and psychometric testing. A fair and equitable review of your skills, background, and motivations will take place by the Recruitment Team.   Shortlisted applicants will attend an assessment session - What to expect?  A chance for you to bring your best self and hear from us, you will undertake an assessment centre day in September and specific activity aligned to the business area.   Offers  Formal offers and pre-employment checks are undertaken including a medical for specific roles.   Commence Graduate program in February 2025!  Ampol's grad program goes for two years and involves four six-month rotations.    Power your career with Ampol today! Applications close on Sunday 18th August 2024.   We're an equal-opportunity workplace. We not only embrace diversity and inclusion; we celebrate what makes you unique. We welcome graduate applications from all cultural backgrounds and diverse sexualities and genders (including if you identify as transgender). We also highly encourage Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander students to apply for the graduate program with Ampol. We are proud to be recognised as an employer of choice for women by WORK180 and are winners of an Employer Brand award through LinkedIn.    We offer:    Unlock Your Potential with Ampol's Benefits:   At Ampol, we're committed to nurturing the next generation of talent. Our graduate benefits are designed to propel your career forward while ensuring your personal and professional well-being. Here's some of the benefits you can expect to receive as a participant of our graduate program:   Our total remuneration is above market! We also offer an Employee Share Scheme so you can invest in your future   25% Fuel discount card for two privately used cars and Novated Lease options are also available   We are flexible! Hybrid work options are available for most disciplines   Career development and learning opportunities including LinkedIn Learning and other tailored training solutions.  We value recognition! We have an internal recognition platform amplifying the achievements of those who do great work and demonstrate our capabilities and values.   Care for your Community - Spend one paid day a year volunteering with one of our Ampol Foundation partners.  Be Mindful! Take up to three Wellbeing Days on Ampol each year, based on a healthy leave balance.   Visit the Ampol Benefits page via the Work180 website to find out more about our policies!

title: Retail Technology Assistant
description: An exciting opportunity exists for a highly skilled and motivated Retail Technology Assistant to work within a vibrant supportive team.
jobType: About Australian United Retailers (AUR)  Australian United Retailers Ltd. (AUR) is a support office for independently owned supermarkets, convenience stores, and liquor retailers. Trading under well-known retail brands such as FoodWorks, Farmer Jacks, and LiquorWorks, we focus on strengthening our retailers' growth and sustainability.    Position Summary  We are seeking a highly skilled and motivated Retail Technology Assistant.The Retail Technology Assistant role is diverse role responsible for providing IT support, network assistance and a range of retail-based accountabilities. This role is crucial for the successful onboarding of our stores to our loyalty program, providing support for integration between POS systems and the loyalty provider, and assisting in the day-to-day operations of the loyalty system. In addition to this you will be assisting the wider technology team with interactionsincluding but not limited to telecommunications, broadband, gift cards, daily scan data collection, online shopping, and internal data cleansing.    The ideal candidate will have a strong technical & business background and the ability to translate technical matters into non-technical business processes.    Key Responsibilities  Onboarding Stores: Lead the onboarding process for new stores joining our loyalty program, ensuring a smooth and efficient transition. Integration Support: Provide expert support for the integration of POS systems with our loyalty provider, troubleshooting and resolving any issues that arise. Daily Operations: Assist in the day-to-day operations of the loyalty system, including monitoring performance, addressing any technical issues, and ensuring the system runs smoothly. Road mapping Enhancements: Develop and maintain a roadmap for enhancements to the loyalty system, working closely with stakeholders to prioritize and implement new features. Communication: Translate complex technical concepts into clear, non-technical language for business stakeholders. Ensure excellent communication both spoken and written. Documentation: Write and maintain comprehensive technical and knowledge base documentation to support the loyalty system and its users. Team Collaboration: Work collaboratively with various teams to see the bigger picture and contribute to the overall success of the loyalty program. Autonomous Work: Capable of working independently with minimal supervision while maintaining high standards and meeting deadlines. Business Focus: Maintain a strong focus on business objectives, ensuring that technical solutions align with business needs and goals. Security Focus: Ensure that all aspects of the loyalty program adhere to security best practices and regulatory requirements. Other relevant duties within the team as required.    Required Qualifications  Proven experience in a similar role, specifically in the retail loyalty space. Strong technical aptitude with the ability to learn and adapt to new technologies quickly. Excellent written and spoken English skills. Demonstrated ability to translate technical matters into non-technical business processes. Keen eye for detail and a strong focus on business objectives. Ability to work both independently and collaboratively within a team. Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to think strategically. Knowledge of POS systems and integration processes. Understanding of security best practices and regulatory requirements in the context of loyalty programs. Proficiency in writing technical and knowledge base documentation.    Preferred Qualifications  Experience with specific loyalty program software or providers. Familiarity with project management tools and methodologies. Background in IT or computer science.    Application Process  To apply, please submit your resume and a cover letter detailing your relevant experience and why you are a perfect fit for this role.    AUR conducts knowledge checks as part of the onboarding process.    Equal Opportunity Employer  Australian United Retailers is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.

title: IT Network Analyst
description: Opportunity for a passionate Network Analyst to join a progressive organisation, with genuine opportunities for career advancement.
salary: Starting salary from $92K; package up to $150K
jobType: Ready to expand on your professional journey with Northern Star Resources? As an ASX 50 global-scale gold miner, we have sizeable operations in Western Australia and Alaska. With unparalleled pathways for career advancement and professional development, we stand proudly as Australia's premier gold employer.  Interested? Your journey starts here..  At Northern Star, we live by our STARR Core Values of Safety, Teamwork, Accountability, Respect & Results. These Values are not just words on paper; they are the cornerstone of our Company culture and guide everything we do. You will play a pivotal role in upholding these values and contributing to our collective growth and continued success.  The Opportunity?  Northern Star currently has great opportunities for two Network Analysts to join us on a permanent, full-time basis. Reporting to the Senior Network Analyst and based at our Subiaco Head Office, these roles are responsible for ensuring Northern Star's business, operational technology and other supporting systems provide constantly reliable and secure communication services.  Responsibilities of the role include:  Implement and support data and voice network solutions providing enough capacity, availability, performance, reliability, and security to support current and future business requirements in compliance with the Information Technology Policy. Hands on management of network operations to include connectivity issues, installing and maintaining network equipment, and monitoring and reporting operational status. Participate in the on-call roster, and while on-call be available for remote support for occasional urgent support issues via call, text message, or Teams. Provide advice on IT security best practices and ensure compliance with the Information Technology Policy. Maintain up to date network diagrams, monitoring dashboards, and hardware and software registers in support of the Company data and voice networks. Monitor the IT Service Desk and ensure that network support incidents are dealt with in a timely manner, and support incidents are escalated to IT management when required. Promoting timely reporting of security incidents and aiding in the identification of and implementation of remedial actions in accordance with the Security Incident Management Plan. Work with site operations managers to ensure that Operational Technology systems comply with the Operational Technology Policy. Implement, maintain, and test backup and disaster recovery plans for network infrastructure.  About you?  With extensive (3+ years) experience supporting IT network infrastructure, you have had exposure to multi-vendor routing & switching, VLAN segregation and subnet design, firewall config & management, cloud networking & security, NAT, VPN, DNS, DHCP and wireless, along with a genuine passion for delivering quality outcomes across your portfolio.  The following will also see you set for success in this role:  A Tertiary Qualification majoring in computer studies, along with Cisco CCNA (or higher) certification or equivalent demonstrable work experience across large multi-site organisations, with multi-vendor networks. ITIL certification or experience working within an ITIL framework would be highly regarded. Familiarity with Operational Technology architectures, including security standards and frameworks applicable to OT environments (IEC 62443, NIST SP 800-82). Experience designing, implementing, operating, and supporting technologies including firewalls, network optimisation services, Ubiquiti, Cisco Meraki and Ruckus wireless, and AWS or Azure networking skills is desirable. Demonstrated ability to maintain or exceed best industry practice in implementing and supporting IT network systems. Working knowledge in supporting common desktop and server applications (Microsoft Windows Client and Server, Active Directory, NPS, Office 365, certificates, endpoint protection etc). Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to build strong rapport and collaborate effectively across a diverse range of stakeholders and cross-functional teams. Well organised, you possess a high level of integrity, professionalism and confidentiality, coupled with an excellent attention to detail. Customer service driven, you are comfortable adapting to changing priorities, with the ability to prioritise & multitask effectively, in a dynamic, outcome focused environment. Solutions focused, with strong problem-solving & analytical skills, and the ability to think outside the box and on your feet.  Discover the perks of working at Northern Star..  Joining the Northern Star team also offers the opportunity to enjoy our industry leading benefits and bonus programs, which include:  Opportunities for career progression & professional development. Heavily subsidised top-tier cover Health Insurance with GU Health. A quarterly Gold Price Variable Bonus. An annual Short-term Incentive Bonus. An annual Employee Share Plan Program. Company paid Salary Continuance Insurance (income protection) from commencement.  Interested?  Northern Star's pre-employment process includes completing a full pre-employment medical, confirmation you hold the relevant Australian work rights, and have the ability to apply for an Australian National Police Clearance.  Northern Star is an equal opportunity employer and fosters an environment that is inclusive and supportive of a diverse workforce.  We genuinely welcome your interest in Northern Star and encourage your application, by clicking the yellow 'Apply Now' button.

This role offers uncapped training and development opportunities as well as other benefits including free parking, flexible working and different leave arrangements including paid parental, study, reserve and volunteer leave. Inclusion - We like our employees to feel safe bringing their whole self to work offering a number of programs promoting inclusion such as, Public Holiday swap and 40/40/20 our vision for a gender inclusive workplace. Benefits and Rewards  Jacobs have a competitive package of benefits and rewards including: Additional superannuation ; Flexible leave options; Salary continuation insurance; Stock purchase plan; Professional certification bonus; Corporate discount program. Exciting work  Jacobs are continually expanding our opportunities working on prominent defence projects across air, land and sea supporting the critical capabilities that keep Australia safe. Jacobs have a strong geographic foothold in Australia, with around 2500 people working across two lines of business  Critical Mission Solutions (CMS) and People & Place Solutions. Apply today to becomes a member and experience the many benefits and rewards that help create a World where you can.   Recruitment selection for these positions will commence immediately. This role will manage a range of Database Platforms, Job Scheduling and Data Integration systems to the required business standards for system Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability and Compliance.    What will your key responsibilities include?  Stakeholder Support: Providing support and technical expertise to key stakeholders regarding problem-solving, inquiries, and design. Providing Production Support: Ensuring the smooth operation of our database systems by monitoring performance, troubleshooting issues, and providing timely resolutions. Database Performance Tuning: Reviewing database queries and stored procedures, scripting, and maintaining optimal performance for our key banking applications. Monitoring and Troubleshooting: Vigilantly overseeing our database environments to pre-empt and address any performance or stability issues. ETL Development: Applying a hands-on approach with end-to-end ETL development in a production environment. Database Structure Alterations: Undertaking alterations to database structures to meet the needs of developers, stakeholders, and changes in business volumes. You will be empowered to make a significant impact by ensuring our systems are robust and efficient,  5 years experience as a MS SQL or Oracle Database Administrator SQL Server (or Oracle) database structures, interfaces and layered products knowledge required Excellent problem solving and analytical skills Excellent communication skills will allow you to work closely with all areas of the business, including technical and non-technical stakeholders Migration exposure desired Cloud experience or genuine interest in this technology is highly regarded Degree, postgraduate, diploma or higher education qualifications in a relevant IT field desirable    What can you expect from us?  NGM Group employees can take advantage of the following work perks:  Health and wellbeing; Fitness passport, corporate health insurance and annual flu vaccination. Lifestyle and giving back; Hotel discounts, 14 weeks paid parental leave, two community volunteers days and three recreational leave days per year. Professional advancement; Flexible work arrangements, recognition programs and employee referral program.    About us  Were NGM Group, and we offer retail banking services to more than half a million Australians under the brands Greater Bank and Newcastle Permanent. We have fresh energy and big goals for our customers, and our people are key to us achieving this success. If youre ready to be part of a team that puts the customer first and enjoys a challenge as the path to growth and innovation, then  we want you! title: Network & Infrastructure Administrator
description: Halcyon Knights is recruiting a Network & Infrastructure Administrator to join a council in the north eastern suburbs for a 12-month contract.
jobType: Halcyon Knights is recruiting a Network & Infrastructure Administrator to join an esteemed council in the north eastern suburbs for a fixed-term 12-month contract.  ABOUT THE ROLE You will be responsible for delivering exceptional customer service while providing support and advice on the Councils ICT Network and Security environments. This role involves diagnosing and repairing hardware and technical software issues.  Technical Knowledge  Infrastructure/Network Support:  Maintain records for all network and technology assets, including leases and licenses. Identify and report risks related to network and infrastructure tasks. Plan and coordinate backup procedures with periodic integrity testing. Keep technical documentation current for all specifications, processes, and procedures. Resolve complex issues across the Councils network, server, and device technologies. Provide 2nd level support and training to the Service Desk to improve their technical abilities. Automate infrastructure and network services, including backups, updates, and patching. Offer ICT support and advice to customers. Install and support Windows servers, VMWare, MS365, MS SQL Server, SANs, Active Directory, and network security solutions. Maintain hardware inventory and documentation. Monitor and ensure optimal performance of the Councils technical systems and network.  Technical Knowledge - Security Support:  Implement and monitor network security strategies and procedures. Protect systems from unauthorized access, modification, and destruction. Scan and assess network vulnerabilities. Develop and implement disaster recovery plans. Stay updated on security and technology trends, vulnerabilities, and breaches; recommend upgrades and security standards. Configure and support security tools such as firewalls, filtering, and anti-virus/EDR software. Report risks related to security and network duties.  ABOUT YOU  Extensive experience with Microsoft environments, including Active Directory & Microsoft Exchange. Proficiency with Microsoft Server and other operating systems. Strong understanding of LAN/WAN environments and remote access solutions. Knowledge of networking concepts: VLAN, VPN, trunk, routing, and TCP/IP. Experience diagnosing and resolving server hardware or software faults. Experience with SOE image development, deployment, and management for PCs and servers. Application and patch management in medium to large enterprises. Supporting cloud-based "X as a Service" platforms (e.g., Office365, Financials, Assets, Payroll, CRM). Configuring routers, modems, and wireless access points. Planning and performing server software updates and upgrades. Supporting medium to large-scale business systems. VMware technology, including managing ESX hosts and hardware, and maintaining virtual environments and servers. Network security, firewalls, and routers. Enterprise storage administration. Voice Over IP technology. Up-to-date with emerging security and technology trends, vulnerabilities, and breaches.  What You Will Receive  The opportunity to work with an esteemed council and its stakeholders A collaborative and supportive team culture Flexibility in your role and work environment  If you meet the above qualifications and are interested, please apply now or email chantelleo@halcyonknights.com.au for any questions.

title: Data Engineer
description: Build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources.
salary: Salary from $92K; package up to $150K inc. super
jobType: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to recruit Data Engineers to work in our Technology and Security Division. These are permanent, ongoing positions at the APS 6 and Executive Level 1 classification levels.  The purpose of the Technology and Security Division is to secure, build, deliver and maintain ICT infrastructure and platforms in support of ABS mission of collecting, collating and disseminating official statistics to support decision making across Australias public and private sectors.  These roles will suit passionate ICT professionals wanting to contribute to the ongoing development, support and uplift of ABS technology solutions.  As a Data Engineer at the ABS you will have responsibility to build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources using Python/R/SQL/Apache Spark and AWS big data technologies. You will be required to work in partnership with ABS business areas and with suppliers to assemble complex ABS data, and to optimise data pipelines that meet business requirements.  To be considered for a Data Engineer position, you will need most, or all of the following skills, qualities and experience:  demonstrated experience building data pipelines and wrangling data experience in optimising data systems and the ability to assemble large, complex data sets that meet functional /non-functional business requirements a proven ability to work with multiple stakeholders as part of a multi-disciplinary agile team by fostering positive working relationships a proven ability to collaborate on IT design and IT best practice, security policies and guidelines, including clearly communicating technical concepts with technical and non-technical audiences a proven ability to apply DevOps practices and automation to the solution you are responsible for delivering demonstrated experience in public cloud platforms, services, and any of the following relevant products is highly desirable:  oCoding Languages (Python and/or R and/or SQL and/or Apache Spark)  oOrchestration and Automation (Lambda, Step Functions)  oDevOps Tools (Gitlab, AWS CodeCommit/Build/Deploy/Pipeline)  oETL tools (Informatica, Glue)  oInfrastructure as Code (CloudFormation, AWS Cloud Development Kit).  Executive Level 1 (EL 1) Application Developer  To be considered for an EL 1 Application Developer position you will need proven experience in some or all of the following:  significant applications development/data engineering experience technical leadership experience managing teams: this may include planning, tracking and reporting progress, and identifying and addressing impediments to ensure successful and on-time delivery of complex projects across multiple IT teams.  To be eligible to apply for these roles you must be an Australian citizen at the time you apply.  How to apply  To apply, complete an online application form on the ABS e-recruitment system. You will need to upload your current resume, provide referee details and respond to the following:  In 750 words or less, please provide an example that best demonstrates applying your Data Engineering or Application Development technical and/or leadership skills to deliver an IT solution that met business needs. Clearly articulate what your role and contribution was and the business benefits achieved, in the context of the selection criteria.  Note:  If you wish to be considered for more than one APS classification level you only need to submit one statement pitched at the EL 1 level.  We are also recruiting for Application Developers as part of this recruitment process.If you wish to apply for both the Application Developer and the Data Engineer roles you only need to submit one statement.  Applications close 11.30 p.m. (AEST) Wednesday 14th August 2024.

title: Infrastructure Architect

jobType: Infrastructure Architect $144,374 $167,369 + 15.4% super Location: Canberra, Brisbane, Sydney, Melbourne WFH and Office Ongoing  ABOUT THE ROLE  The Infrastructure Architect is responsible for scoping and designing the overarching Cloud solution and infrastructure designs (High & Low level) in conjunction with Subject Matter Experts, Infrastructure and Operations, Project Managers and peer Architects. Collaboration:Work closely with other IT teams, developers, and stakeholders to design and implement effective solutions. AAD/Entra ID, Active Directory, ADFS, synchronisation, Identity Management and Access management MS Office, MS Teams and M365 services. MS Windows Server2012-2022and related services. Note: Information about our terms and conditions of employment are contained in the AMSA Enterprise Agreement 2024 - 2027  AMSA BENEFITS  We are committed a supportive and collaborative work environment, which is why AMSA offers:  Flexible work including work from home arrangements Health and wellbeing programs including annual flu vaccinations and a healthy lifestyle reimbursement An office-wide Christmas period shutdown (in addition to annual leave provisions) An ability to work for an organisation charged with protecting our marine environments and saving lives  ABOUT AMSA  The Australian Maritime Safety Authority (AMSA) is responsible for the safety of international shipping and domestic commercial vessels, protection of the environment from ship sourced pollution and search and rescue nationally.  AMSA offers unique and interesting career opportunities, and we employ around 450 people across Australia.To learn more about our organisation please visit our website.  DIVERSITY AND INCLUSION  Diversity and inclusion are a priority at AMSA.  Our role means that we impact and influence communities right across Australia, this is why it is essential that we draw on the diversity of our people to successfully deliver our mission ofensuring safe vessel operations, combatting marine pollution and rescuing people in distress. HOW TO APPLY  Please complete your application on our website via the Careers at AMSA page by 11:55pm 16 August 2024. For any questions regarding the role please contact Anupuri, Abhishek on 02 89181345  If you have any questions about the recruitment process please contact Human Resources on recruitment@amsa.gov.au  AMSA does not engage staff under the Public Service Act 1999. AMSA engages employees under the Australian Maritime Safety Authority Act 1990 and our remuneration arrangements are specific to AMSA.

title: Network Engineer - Autonomous Systems
description: The successful candidate will lead the rapid development of a common command and control system for Defence.
jobType: Applications close 17 August 2024  Target start date 26 August 2024  Brisbane based position    Autonomous Systems Network Engineer  Trusted Autonomous Systems (TAS) requires an experienced network engineer keen to work directly with TAS - a proven innovation specialist in the Robotics, Autonomous Systems and Artificial Intelligence (RAS-AI) domain - and our Defence partners, to accelerate RAS-AI technology transfer into capability.  About Trusted Autonomous Systems  TAS (initially established as Australias first Defence cooperative research centre) is an innovation R&D house uniquely equipped to deliver world-leading robotic and autonomous systems with artificial intelligence (RAS-AI) to enable trusted and effective cooperation between humans and machines. TAS conducts disruptive innovation in trusted autonomous systems to transform the ADF and grow sovereign Australian capabilities.  Our aim is to foster a competitive, productive and sustainable Australian industry primed to develop and deliver world-leading autonomous and robotic Defence technologies; build innovative Intellectual Property through targeted research and technology programs; and assist Australian industry to evaluate and showcase innovative autonomous technologies through capability demonstrations.  Specifically, TAS:  develops highly self-sufficient and survivable systems develops highly self-determining and self-aware systems develops human-autonomy systems that are human and context aware increases the speed to reach a deployable state for trusted autonomous systems increases the scalability and reduce the cost of autonomous systems technology solutions educates in the ethics and legal aspects of autonomous systems informs national policy and regulation discussions    About TAS Projects  TAS projects are defence-driven, industry-led and research-based, delivering sustainable disruptive autonomous systems capability to the nation, driven by our ambition to transform how Defence fights and wins. The current portfolio of projects is extensive, spanning operational domains and key enablers, with strong growth in the scale and scope of the portfolio expected in the years ahead.  Projects align to our smart, small and many vision, exploiting AI, miniaturisation and new methods of manufacturing to develop low-cost autonomous systems that can be deployed at scale to create unprecedented mass and combat weight advantages, leading to greater freedom of manoeuvre for the commander. Systems developed through projects not only deliver game-changing capabilities, but also adhere to the legal, regulatory and ethical frameworks governing Defence, ensuring trusted autonomy aligned to social expectations and national and international obligations.  Projects grow sustainable sovereign Australian industry capability, strengthen industry-academic partnership, promote research-translation, and act as change agents, providing Defence with new tools to shape, deter and respond. We are committed to the fail-fast approach, accepting measured but significant innovation risk in our program, and adapting effort, direction and investment accordingly to maximise impact for Defence and the nation.  Projects are commercially sensitive, and so limited information is available to external audiences. However, a few examples of the scale and ambition of our projects can be foundon our website what we do and news.  About the Role  The successful candidate will lead the networking and communications elements in the rapid development of a common command and control system for Defence. The system will be used to support structured experimentation of developmental robotic and autonomous systems in operational scenarios, with an initial focus on an integrated common C2 system for multi-robot operations in the land domain. The successful candidate can also expect to participate across other projects in the maritime and air domains.  You will work with the TAS Chief Technology Officer Team and other important stakeholders, including our Defence partners, to enhance the system architecture, implement design, and support test and evaluation activities. You will work with the project lead and senior software engineer to guide the project toward short-term delivery (<1 year), with key milestones in September 2024 and June 2025. You will support software development activities as appropriate and participate in field experimentation of the common C2 solution.  TAS is headquartered in Brisbane, this is a Brisbane based position.  The role is scoped for a full-time applicant for 12 months, with potential for extension. The successful applicant will ultimately take on an expanded role across two other programmes due to commence in the next financial year, forming a core part of the growing TAS delivery team. This is an exciting opportunity to contribute during the early phases of a potentially significant expansion of TAS technical program.  Remuneration  Remuneration for this position is set at >$165,000 plus superannuation, dependent upon the experience of the successful applicant.  About You  You must have a results-driven and proactive approach to development. To meet rapid development timeframes, you must be comfortable working collaboratively, making prioritisation decisions, and communicating risk. You are familiar with, or willing to learn about, command and control concepts and technologies as they apply to autonomous systems, heterogeneous teams, and Defence activities.  You will demonstrate flexibility in your contribution to development and deployment efforts and must be capable of ready discussion with stakeholders to ensure delivery in accordance with expectations. You should have sufficient experience to support independent work and the ability to make informed decisions on behalf of the software team to achieve project objectives.  Essential Requirements  The following requirements are mandatory:  Experience in network architecture specification and implementation. Expert knowledge of Wireless WAN/LAN, Ethernet, VPNs and various network topologies. Experience with Linux-based operating systems and networks. Experience with rapid/agile development processes. Experience with hardware/software integration. Experience with software containerisation and deployment technologies including Docker Experience with third-party product integration. Experience with collaborative software development environments. Reside in Australia. Currently hold, or be eligible to hold, an AGSVA security clearance at NV1.  Desirable Requirements  The following requirements are desirable:  An understanding of command and control functions and architectures, relevant standards and protocols. Previous experience in a DevOps role Experience with acoustic communications. Familiarity with Defence experimentation or Defence operations. Proficiency in at least one compiled programming language, e.g. Go, Java or C++. Application  To apply, submit applications via the Seek job listing. Applications must include a cover letter addressing the selection criteria, a CV, and two current references by COB 17 August 2024  Questions can be directed to info@tasdcrc.com.au.

title: Data Engineer
description: Build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources.
jobType: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to recruit Data Engineers to work in our Technology and Security Division. These are permanent, ongoing positions at the APS 6 and Executive Level 1 classification levels.  The purpose of the Technology and Security Division is to secure, build, deliver and maintain ICT infrastructure and platforms in support of ABS mission of collecting, collating and disseminating official statistics to support decision making across Australias public and private sectors.  These roles will suit passionate ICT professionals wanting to contribute to the ongoing development, support and uplift of ABS technology solutions.  As a Data Engineer at the ABS you will have responsibility to build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources using Python/R/SQL/Apache Spark and AWS big data technologies. You will be required to work in partnership with ABS business areas and with suppliers to assemble complex ABS data, and to optimise data pipelines that meet business requirements.  To be considered for a Data Engineer position, you will need most, or all of the following skills, qualities and experience:  demonstrated experience building data pipelines and wrangling data experience in optimising data systems and the ability to assemble large, complex data sets that meet functional /non-functional business requirements a proven ability to work with multiple stakeholders as part of a multi-disciplinary agile team by fostering positive working relationships a proven ability to collaborate on IT design and IT best practice, security policies and guidelines, including clearly communicating technical concepts with technical and non-technical audiences a proven ability to apply DevOps practices and automation to the solution you are responsible for delivering demonstrated experience in public cloud platforms, services, and any of the following relevant products is highly desirable:  oCoding Languages (Python and/or R and/or SQL and/or Apache Spark)  oOrchestration and Automation (Lambda, Step Functions)  oDevOps Tools (Gitlab, AWS CodeCommit/Build/Deploy/Pipeline)  oETL tools (Informatica, Glue)  oInfrastructure as Code (CloudFormation, AWS Cloud Development Kit).  Executive Level 1 (EL 1) Application Developer  To be considered for an EL 1 Application Developer position you will need proven experience in some or all of the following:  significant applications development/data engineering experience technical leadership experience managing teams: this may include planning, tracking and reporting progress, and identifying and addressing impediments to ensure successful and on-time delivery of complex projects across multiple IT teams.  To be eligible to apply for these roles you must be an Australian citizen at the time you apply.  How to apply  To apply, complete an online application form on the ABS e-recruitment system. You will need to upload your current resume, provide referee details and respond to the following:  In 750 words or less, please provide an example that best demonstrates applying your Data Engineering or Application Development technical and/or leadership skills to deliver an IT solution that met business needs. Clearly articulate what your role and contribution was and the business benefits achieved, in the context of the selection criteria.  Note:  If you wish to be considered for more than one APS classification level you only need to submit one statement pitched at the EL 1 level.  We are also recruiting for Application Developers as part of this recruitment process.If you wish to apply for both the Application Developer and the Data Engineer roles you only need to submit one statement.  Applications close 11.30 p.m. (AEST) Wednesday 14th August 2024.

title: Senior Systems Integrator
description: Provide high level advice to Queensland Health projects and programs on the capacity, resource requirements and timeframes
jobType: The successful candidate will provide high level advice to Queensland Health projects and programs on the capacity, resource requirements and timeframes to deliver interfacing solutions of a varying complexity.  Role responsibilities:  Manage collaborative relationships and consult with key project stakeholders across Queensland Health and external application vendors to advise, analyse, design and develop solutions to meet clinical application data integration requirements. Liaise and negotiate with internal and external stakeholders, with a customer service focus, to resolve issues relating to priorities, technical concepts, key technical decisions, scheduling, and Queensland Health's change management processes. Manage and execute the end-to-end software development processes for implementing new application integration interfaces at varying levels of complexity on Queensland Health's messaging infrastructure, including managing the interactions with the client project staff, to deliver successful business outcomes. Provide ongoing support and maintenance, including monitoring and troubleshooting, of clinical application integration interfaces in accordance with service level agreements and application interface specifications. Other duties as specified by the supervisor/line manager.  You will be assessed on your ability to demonstrate the following key capabilities, knowledge and experience. Within the context of the responsibilities described above under Key Responsibilities', the ideal applicant will be someone who can demonstrate the following:  Familiarity with the ITIL methodology and processes (SFIA: METL Level 4) Demonstrated ability to develop and maintain relationships with key internal project stakeholders and external application vendors in order to deliver the required healthcare outcomes (SFIA: RLMT Level 5) Demonstrated interpersonal, consultation, negotiation and communication skills to enable effective interaction with technical and non-technical staff (NHS: Effective and strategic influencing) Demonstrated ability to prioritise tasks to ensure deadlines are achieved (NHS: Self Management) Knowledge of Rhapsody Development (SFIA: TECH Level 5)  Specific working conditions:  Variable hours: Weekend and afterhours work may be required (at various locations in Queensland as determined by business needs) and may be requested at short notice. While not mandatory, any relevant qualifications in Information Communication Technology or similar, would be highly desirable. This position may be required to work at different sites. The position may be required to work outside of standard business hours.  Benefits of working with eHealth Queensland:  By joining eHealth Queensland, you will work within a fast-paced, challenging and supportive environment where every employee plays a critical role in our ongoing success.  You will enjoy a variety of benefits, including:  Competitive salary + generous superannuation and leave loading Flexible working arrangements Diverse work culture Career training and development  To apply for this exciting opportunity, submit your resume and a cover letter (maximum 2 pages) online today.

title: Workplace Services Solution Engineer
description: Solution Engineer opportunity for large, iconic market leader, Boral. Make an impact for a business with cutting edge technology stack and tools.
salary: Salary from $92K; package up to $150K inc. super
jobType: Your next opportunity  An opportunity exists for a Workplace Services Solution Engineer to join Borals broader IT Team. Reporting to the IT Operations Lead, the Solution Engineer will deliver and support the digital solutions that enable Boral, with a mandate to provide excellent systems experiences for Borals customers, operations and employees alike. Solution Engineers own the entire delivery value chain and contribute effectively to analysis, design, development, testing, deployment and operations support.  Your day will involve:  Learn and master Boral systems and business processes in order to create fit for purpose and cost effective solutions that solve customer needs across IT infrastructure at Boral including desktops, laptops, software, user authentication etc Understand the Boral architecture and design principles and develop solutions that respect these principles Understand the Boral business operations and proactively suggest features and changes that could be incorporated into products and systems to enhance user experience and internal productivity Undertake production deployment and service transition activities Provide operations support, utilising proactive tools and techniques to anticipate and then rapidly address issues as they arise.  What are we looking for?  Demonstrated relevant experience in a customer facing similar role with the ability to communicate technical concepts and specifications clearly and efficiently. Demonstrated ability to deliver on a range of technical tasks such as analysis, design, development, testing, operations. Expert level understanding in the implementation, configuration and support of Microsoft Intune / Autopilot (MDM and Software Packaging) and Azure EntraId with experience with troubleshooting packaging and deployment issues. Good level of understanding and experience in the implementation, configuration and support of Microsoft SCCM and Adaptiva. Experience with troubleshooting of build failures of EntraId joined machines. Experience with Windows 11, Windows 11 customizations and SOE. Good level of understanding and experience in the administration of Microsoft Active Directory.  Whats on offer?  Attractive salary package reflective of your skills and experience Genuine career growth opportunities within Boral Ongoing mentoring and guidance from industry leaders and subject matter experts Broaden your horizons through exposure to our integrated operations Modern offices and workstations, close to public transport options and with free on-site parking Work for a values-based business that shares goals and celebrates individual and team success Work for an Equal Opportunity Employer  At Boral, we understand that diversity brings many benefits, and we are increasingly encouraging greater diversity within our workplaces We are Australian-owned and operated Opportunity to purchase additional leave Generous paid parental leave entitlements.  About Boral  We are Australias leading vertically-integrated construction materials solution provider and have been helping to build and enable a strong, modern Australia for more than 75 years. Our integrated network includes upstream assets  quarries, cement operations and our bitumen JV - and downstream operations across, recycling, concrete and concrete placing and asphalt.  Our people provide solutions to help customers and stakeholders build a sustainable future in a changing world. Our values are what matters to us and guide our behaviours: Safety, Teamwork, Ambition, Accountability andRespect.  Were proud of our legacy as a great Australian business and have a strong foundation to improve and continue fulfilling our purpose and what we do best - building something great.  Boral values and is committed to creating a diverse working environment and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All suitable applicants will receive consideration foremployment without regard to race, colour, religion, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, disability or age.
