title: Support Team Leader
description: The Support Team Leader will be responsible for managing a team of support agents, ensuring exceptional service delivery.
salary: Salary from $92K; package up to $150K inc. super
jobType: We are seeking a dynamic and experienced Support Team Leader to join our customer support department at MEX. MEX is a leading software company that specializes in developing cutting-edge solutions for CMMS (Computerized Maintenance Management System) software.  The Support Team Leader will be responsible for managing a team of support agents, ensuring exceptional service delivery, and driving continuous improvement in support processes. This role requires a blend of technical proficiency, leadership skills, and a passion for customer satisfaction and will report to the Product Manager.  Key Responsibilities  Team Management:  Lead, mentor, and motivate a team of support agents to achieve performance goals and deliver high-quality customer service. Conduct regular performance reviews, provide constructive feedback, and identify opportunities for professional development.  Customer Support Oversight:  Oversee daily support operations, including handling escalated customer issues, managing ticket queues, and ensuring timely resolution of support requests. Ensure adherence to company support standards and procedures.  Process Improvement:  Analyse support metrics and customer feedback to identify trends and areas for improvement. Develop and implement strategies to enhance support processes, increase efficiency, and improve customer satisfaction.  Collaboration:  Work closely with other departments, such as Product Development and Sales, to address customer feedback, resolve complex issues, and improve overall product quality. Participate in cross-functional projects as needed.  Reporting and Analysis:  Perform analysis on the support team performance, customer satisfaction, and key performance indicators (KPIs) to senior management. Use data-driven insights to guide decision-making and strategic planning.  Customer Relationship Management:  Foster strong relationships with key customers and act as a point of contact for high-priority or complex support issues. Ensure a high level of customer satisfaction and retention.    Qualifications  Education:  Bachelors degree in computer science, Business Administration, or a related field as preferred but not required. Relevant certifications or training in customer support or management are a plus.  Experience:  Minimum of 3 years of experience in a customer support role, with at least 1-2 years in a supervisory or team lead position, preferably in the software or technology industry.  Technical Skills:  Strong understanding of software products, technical troubleshooting, and support tools. Familiarity with CRM systems, helpdesk software, and support ticketing systems.  Leadership Skills:  Proven ability to lead and inspire a team, manage performance, and drive results. Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to handle sensitive situations with professionalism and empathy.  Analytical Skills:  Strong problem-solving abilities and experience using data to drive improvements. Ability to analyse trends and make data-driven decisions.  Customer Focus:  A passion for delivering exceptional customer service and a track record of achieving high levels of customer satisfaction.

title: Head of Enterprise AI
description: Our new Head of Enterprise AI will be the captain of this ship, steering us through the uncharted waters of AI creativity. They'll ensure that we'r...
jobType: We are thrilled to announce a groundbreaking opportunity to join the Sportsbet team - the role of Head of Enterprise AI  This isn't just a new position; it's a new frontier for our company, and we're not just stepping into itwe're leaping with both feet and a jetpack!  Why, you ask? Because embracing Generative AI is like upgrading from a flip phone to the latest smartphone. It's not just about being on the cutting edge; it's about holding the scissors. Generative AI is the powerhouse behind innovations that can write code, create art, and even draft emails funnier than this one (hard to believe, I know).  In an innovative technology company like ours, staying ahead isn't just a goal; it's our mantra. Generative AI is the secret sauce that will help us cook up solutions we haven't even dreamed of yet. It's like having a crystal ball, but instead of vague predictions, it gives us solid prototypes.  Our new Head of Enterprise AI will be the captain of this ship, steering us through the uncharted waters of AI creativity. They'll ensure that we're not just using AI, but that we're also creating with it, innovating with it, and maybe even making it our plus-one at company parties.  So, let's give a warm welcome to this new role and the brave soul who will fill it. Together, we're not just building software; we're building the future. And trust me, the future is looking as bright as our screens at full brightness - so you might want to put on some sunglasses.  Here's to innovation, imagination, and a touch of AI-generated humor!  The Perks  We work hard and play hard, so along with a competitive salary and generous performance-based bonus, we will also provide you with:  25 days annual leave (a whole extra week of holidays!) Genuine flexible working and remote working policy with a $1050 work from home office allowance Development budget to send you to conferences, events, courses and other learning opportunities. Weekly concierge service including free massages, manicure/nail appointments  all onsite! Daily fresh fruit, free breakfast, sparkling water and Kombucha on tap in the office (did we mention we have a Thursday afternoon social hour?) Tailored career development programs with a yearly tools down day to focus on goals End of trip facilities with an onsite table tennis and pool table Access to our employee assistance program and a Circle In membership Were proud of our industry leading Parental Leave support program with 26 weeks paid leave for Primary Carers with no waiting time and two weeks of paid leave for Secondary Carers followed by six weeks unpaid leave. We also have a progressive return to work benefits for your first six months back: come back for three days, get paid for four; come back for four days, get paid for five. Get the Green Tick Feeling - the feeling you get when you Thrive working at Sportsbet!  Whats the Green Tick Feeling?  Well, its different for everyone, yet unites us all. Its the feeling you get when you succeed, no matter what success looks like to you. It could be developing your career, it could be working on an industry leading project, or it could be making it to school pick up in time. It's all the little and big things that make you feel like youre Thriving working at Sportsbet.  We encourage you to apply as soon as possible as we review candidates within one-two weeks of advertising. Be sure to check out our Life@Sportsbet Instagram page, Sportsbet LinkedIn page as well our careers website for more information and insight into our culture.   Ready for your Green Tick Feeling? Apply now

title: Partner Solution Architecture- Modern Work
description: Guide the development of business solutions, provide deep technical insights, and accelerate the growth of Microsoft Tech priorities
salary: Starting salary from $92K; package up to $150K
jobType: Overview  The Global Partner Solutions (GPS) team is a sales organization accountable for the commercial partner business at Microsoft, and the mission is to build and sell Microsoft Cloud applications, services and devices with partners, empowering people, and organizations to achieve more.  As a Partner Solution Architect, you will guide the development of business solutions, provide deep technical insights, and accelerate the growth of Microsoft Tech priorities. You will work closely with partners to understand their technical requirements and business objectives, and guide them through architectural design sessions, developing proof of concepts, and help them transition from legacy systems to modern cloud environments, ensuring that their solutions are optimized for performance and cost-efficiency.  Join our team as a Partner Solution Architect and play a pivotal role in guiding our most significant partners to designing and implementing innovative scalable, secure, and efficient cloud architectures that meet market needs. By leveraging your skills in technical leadership, cloud computing, software development, problem solving and systems architecture, you will drive business impact by enabling digital transformation, optimizing performance, and driving innovation through the effective use of cloud technologies.  Microsofts mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others, and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.  Qualifications  Bachelor's degree in computer science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business or related field AND 4+ years technical consulting, technical consultative selling, product development, or related technical/sales experience OR master's degree in computer science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business or related field AND 3+ years technical consulting, technical consultative selling, product development, or related technical/sales experience OR equivalent experience 6-10+ years of related experience in technology IP solutions or services development, with a deep understanding of digital transformation business drivers, cloud platforms, and emerging cloud trends like generative AI (ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE) and SaaS (Software as a Service) services Strong background and in-depth knowledge of cloud technologies, with a focus on Microsoft's cloud offerings (Azure, Dynamics 365, Microsoft 365) M365 tenant management Security, governance, and data access best practices Adoption and Change management (Prosci) Build Copilot extensions or Windows virtualization  W365 & AVD  Preferred Qualifications (PQs)  Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, or related field AND 8+ years experience in cloud/infrastructure technologies, information technology (IT) consulting/support, systems administration, network operations, software development/support, technology solutions, practice development, architecture, and/or consulting OR Master's Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Business, or related field AND 6+ years experience in cloud/infrastructure technologies, technology solutions, practice development, architecture, and/or consulting OR equivalent experience 4+ years experience working in a customer-facing role (e.g., internal and/or external) 4+ years experience working on technical projects Technical Certification in Cloud (e.g., Azure, Amazon Web Services, Google, security certifications  Responsibilities  Your responsibilities as a Partner Solution Architect will be to:  Design Cloud Architectures - Ensure robust, scalable, and secure cloud infrastructure tailored to partner needs, allowing businesses to handle growth, and changing demands efficiently. Lead Architectural Design Sessions - Facilitate the creation of effective and efficient cloud solutions through collaborative planning and design sessions, ensuring alignment with business goals and technical requirements. This collaboration fosters innovation and problem-solving, leading to better-designed systems. Develop Proof of Concepts and Pilots  Demonstrate the feasibility and benefits of proposed cloud solutions, gaining partner buy-in and driving adoption. These prototypes help validate ideas and identify potential issues before full-scale implementation, saving time and resources. Provide Technical Guidance and Support - Ensure successful implementation and optimization of cloud solutions, enhancing partner satisfaction and solution performance, to maximize the value of partner cloud investments and adapt efficiently to challenges. Transition Partner from Legacy Systems - Facilitate smooth transitions to modern cloud environments, improving efficiency and reducing operational risks for partners, to help them stay competitive by leveraging the latest technologies and cloud best practices. Provide advocacy for Microsoft 365 and Copilot adoption with partners  Assist partners in developing their Adoption and Change Management capabilities around customer adoption and usage of Microsoft 365 Copilot to help achieve the FY25 MCAPS priority of a Copilot on every device.  Benefits/perks listed below may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Microsoft and the country where you work.  Industry leading healthcare Educational resources Discounts on products and services Savings and investments Maternity and paternity leave Generous time away Giving programs Opportunities to network and connect

title: Data Engineer
description: Build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources.
jobType: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to recruit Data Engineers to work in our Technology and Security Division. These are permanent, ongoing positions at the APS 6 and Executive Level 1 classification levels.  The purpose of the Technology and Security Division is to secure, build, deliver and maintain ICT infrastructure and platforms in support of ABS mission of collecting, collating and disseminating official statistics to support decision making across Australias public and private sectors.  These roles will suit passionate ICT professionals wanting to contribute to the ongoing development, support and uplift of ABS technology solutions.  As a Data Engineer at the ABS you will have responsibility to build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources using Python/R/SQL/Apache Spark and AWS big data technologies. You will be required to work in partnership with ABS business areas and with suppliers to assemble complex ABS data, and to optimise data pipelines that meet business requirements.  To be considered for a Data Engineer position, you will need most, or all of the following skills, qualities and experience:  demonstrated experience building data pipelines and wrangling data experience in optimising data systems and the ability to assemble large, complex data sets that meet functional /non-functional business requirements a proven ability to work with multiple stakeholders as part of a multi-disciplinary agile team by fostering positive working relationships a proven ability to collaborate on IT design and IT best practice, security policies and guidelines, including clearly communicating technical concepts with technical and non-technical audiences a proven ability to apply DevOps practices and automation to the solution you are responsible for delivering demonstrated experience in public cloud platforms, services, and any of the following relevant products is highly desirable:  oCoding Languages (Python and/or R and/or SQL and/or Apache Spark)  oOrchestration and Automation (Lambda, Step Functions)  oDevOps Tools (Gitlab, AWS CodeCommit/Build/Deploy/Pipeline)  oETL tools (Informatica, Glue)  oInfrastructure as Code (CloudFormation, AWS Cloud Development Kit).  Executive Level 1 (EL 1) Application Developer  To be considered for an EL 1 Application Developer position you will need proven experience in some or all of the following:  significant applications development/data engineering experience technical leadership experience managing teams: this may include planning, tracking and reporting progress, and identifying and addressing impediments to ensure successful and on-time delivery of complex projects across multiple IT teams.  To be eligible to apply for these roles you must be an Australian citizen at the time you apply.  How to apply  To apply, complete an online application form on the ABS e-recruitment system. You will need to upload your current resume, provide referee details and respond to the following:  In 750 words or less, please provide an example that best demonstrates applying your Data Engineering or Application Development technical and/or leadership skills to deliver an IT solution that met business needs. Clearly articulate what your role and contribution was and the business benefits achieved, in the context of the selection criteria.  Note:  If you wish to be considered for more than one APS classification level you only need to submit one statement pitched at the EL 1 level.  We are also recruiting for Application Developers as part of this recruitment process.If you wish to apply for both the Application Developer and the Data Engineer roles you only need to submit one statement.  Applications close 11.30 p.m. (AEST) Wednesday 14th August 2024.

title: IT Business Analyst
description: Seeking a dynamic and agile IT Business Analyst to join our high achieving Technology and Information Management Team at Atlas Iron.
jobType: Company description:    About Us  Atlas Iron is an Australian owned Iron Ore company, mining and exporting direct shipping ore from its operations in WA's Pilbara Region. Between our Mt Webber, Sanjiv Ridge and Miralga Creek Operations, as well as our active exploration projects, we are expanding into exciting new areas for the future. To support our expanding Operations, we are seeking applications for an outstanding professional to make a difference in our growing team.    Job description:    About the role  Reporting to the Manager IT Portfolio Deliver, the primary purpose of the IT Business Analyst role is to support the efficient delivery of IT initiatives (both projects and BAU) ensuring they are adequately understood and documented from both a delivery and sustainable operation perspective.  The Business Analyst will work either as part of a project team or individually to progress initiatives engaging across internal and external stakeholders.  Main responsibilities of the role include:  Gathering, validating and documenting business requirements. Modelling business processes and identifying opportunities for process improvements. Identifying issues, risks and benefits of existing and proposed solutions and outlining business impacts. Creating functional specifications for solutions. Writing solution documentation including training material. Estimating costs and identifying business savings including preparation of business cases in collaboration with project managers. Simplifying information and deciphering technical jargon so it is easily understood by the broader business. Supporting the implementation and testing of solutions. Supporting business transition and helping to establish change.  About you  You will be a dynamic, self-starter with plenty of enthusiasm and align with our Values of Excellence, Indomitable Spirit, Agility, Trust and Win-Win. You will be an individual who can think outside the box, can work autonomously, have an eye for detail with excellent communication and stakeholder management skills.  To be successful in this role, you will have:  5+ years' experience working as a business analyst Prior experience in mining industry is desirable but not essential Relevant academic qualification and experience Business Analyst certification (IIBA) (desirable) Agile Scrum Management certification (desirable)   Profile description:    About Joining  Atlas Iron provides a competitive remuneration package including attractive incentive programs, flexible work arrangements, genuine fun friendly team culture, and career development opportunities. The average tenure of its staff pays testament to the excellent team culture. Join a growing company, where you can make a difference!  Atlas Iron offers an array of opportunities to great employees - there has never been a better time to join.  Atlas is an equal opportunity employer and we endeavour to attract and retain a diverse workforce.  We encourage females, Aboriginal Australians, those identifying as LGBTIQ+, people of all ages and culturally diverse backgrounds to apply for this role  Interested to learn more about Atlas Iron? Visit www.atlasiron.com.au.

title: Cloud Support Engineer
description: Pronto Software is an established Australian business software developer and vendor looking for a Cloud Support Engineer to join Pronto Cloud.
jobType: About our Cloud Support Engineer Role:  Want to grow your Career working in a virtualised environment built around VMWare, Linux and Windows? How about in a well-established and mature Software Development and vendor Company with more than 1500 clients? Support and collaboration with your team-mates? Were a friendly bunch. Exposure to cross-functional Cloud teams (Infra, Network, Security)  develop your career and experience. Hybrid Work Arrangement: find some flexibility in your working week in consultation with your team (the best of both worlds!)   Where youd be working:  This role is in Milton QLD, working alongside Pronto Cloud (in North Ryde NSW), part of Pronto Software. Pronto Cloud is responsible for delivering IaaS, PaaS & SaaS to support enterprise solutions including the Pronto Xi ERP to our customers. We operate in a virtualised environment built around VMWare, Linux and Windows. Our employees stick around because they enjoy their colleagues, culture and supportive team.    What youd be doing:  You will work as a Level 1 Cloud Support Engineer within our support team. Your teams focus is on providing technical support in relation to Pronto Xi ERP, Cognos business intelligence and various mobile application solutions.    Cloud Support Engineer role details (your day would look like this):  Resolution and response of customer requests Triage and escalation of more complex issues as required General operational activities, e.g. backup verifications, Customer DR testing Documentation Email management Linux Shell Scripting and System Administration. MS Windows Server, SQL, AD & VMWare system Administration. You will gain exposure to: Various operating systems - Linux & MS Windows Server Oracle, IBM Informix and Microsoft SQL Server databases Network and communications, NSX technologies    Were looking for a new Pronto Cloud employee who has:  A relevant information technology qualification (ideal, but not essential) Good level of knowledge with virtualisation Intermediate Microsoft product knowledge such as Windows Server, SQL, Active Directory User authentication including 2FA, Azure AD, Okta Strong knowledge of email systems and management Basic/Intermediate knowledge of Linux-like operating system. Understanding WAN/LAN and remote communications issues, VMWare NSX, VPNs Good understanding of IT security and controls.    To enjoy being a Pronto Cloud Employees youd need:  To possess a strong work ethic Ability to demonstrate your relevant business and functional experience. Ability to influence internal and external stakeholders. Able to demonstrate strong commercial understanding. Excellent attention to detail. To be passionate about customer service and delivery excellence.    What you will get from Pronto Software:  Supportive and collaborative team environment A hybrid working environment (split your week, flexible location arrangements) A cross-functional team (Infra, Network, Security) to expand your knowledge and career potential. The ability to develop your career and experience. Salary commensurate with experience, with annual reviews.  Note: our employees need to undergo a Police Check.    Sounds good? Apply now through Seek, please include a brief letter of application and your CV.    More about Pronto Software:  We are an Australian developer of award-winning business management and analytics solutions. Pronto Xi, our ERP software, integrates accounting, operational and mobile features in a single system  optimising business processes and unlocking actionable insights. Over 1,500 organisations have leveraged our industry experience and innovation to increase growth and revenue.  We have an enviable reputation for employee loyalty and service. Pronto Software survey our staff every year, and were proud we have a very high percentage (high 90s%) of staff who agree that:  They are proud to work at Pronto Software and are passionate about the work they do Staff and managers have a professional and positive attitude Pronto Software achieves the best outcomes for customers and staff Pronto is generous and giving to the community Staff would recommend Pronto Software as a great place to work    Please note:Pronto Software does not use external recruitment services.

title: Network Engineer - Autonomous Systems
description: The successful candidate will lead the rapid development of a common command and control system for Defence.
jobType: Applications close 17 August 2024  Target start date 26 August 2024  Brisbane based position    Autonomous Systems Network Engineer  Trusted Autonomous Systems (TAS) requires an experienced network engineer keen to work directly with TAS - a proven innovation specialist in the Robotics, Autonomous Systems and Artificial Intelligence (RAS-AI) domain - and our Defence partners, to accelerate RAS-AI technology transfer into capability.  About Trusted Autonomous Systems  TAS (initially established as Australias first Defence cooperative research centre) is an innovation R&D house uniquely equipped to deliver world-leading robotic and autonomous systems with artificial intelligence (RAS-AI) to enable trusted and effective cooperation between humans and machines. TAS conducts disruptive innovation in trusted autonomous systems to transform the ADF and grow sovereign Australian capabilities.  Our aim is to foster a competitive, productive and sustainable Australian industry primed to develop and deliver world-leading autonomous and robotic Defence technologies; build innovative Intellectual Property through targeted research and technology programs; and assist Australian industry to evaluate and showcase innovative autonomous technologies through capability demonstrations.  Specifically, TAS:  develops highly self-sufficient and survivable systems develops highly self-determining and self-aware systems develops human-autonomy systems that are human and context aware increases the speed to reach a deployable state for trusted autonomous systems increases the scalability and reduce the cost of autonomous systems technology solutions educates in the ethics and legal aspects of autonomous systems informs national policy and regulation discussions    About TAS Projects  TAS projects are defence-driven, industry-led and research-based, delivering sustainable disruptive autonomous systems capability to the nation, driven by our ambition to transform how Defence fights and wins. The current portfolio of projects is extensive, spanning operational domains and key enablers, with strong growth in the scale and scope of the portfolio expected in the years ahead.  Projects align to our smart, small and many vision, exploiting AI, miniaturisation and new methods of manufacturing to develop low-cost autonomous systems that can be deployed at scale to create unprecedented mass and combat weight advantages, leading to greater freedom of manoeuvre for the commander. Systems developed through projects not only deliver game-changing capabilities, but also adhere to the legal, regulatory and ethical frameworks governing Defence, ensuring trusted autonomy aligned to social expectations and national and international obligations.  Projects grow sustainable sovereign Australian industry capability, strengthen industry-academic partnership, promote research-translation, and act as change agents, providing Defence with new tools to shape, deter and respond. We are committed to the fail-fast approach, accepting measured but significant innovation risk in our program, and adapting effort, direction and investment accordingly to maximise impact for Defence and the nation.  Projects are commercially sensitive, and so limited information is available to external audiences. However, a few examples of the scale and ambition of our projects can be foundon our website what we do and news.  About the Role  The successful candidate will lead the networking and communications elements in the rapid development of a common command and control system for Defence. The system will be used to support structured experimentation of developmental robotic and autonomous systems in operational scenarios, with an initial focus on an integrated common C2 system for multi-robot operations in the land domain. The successful candidate can also expect to participate across other projects in the maritime and air domains.  You will work with the TAS Chief Technology Officer Team and other important stakeholders, including our Defence partners, to enhance the system architecture, implement design, and support test and evaluation activities. You will work with the project lead and senior software engineer to guide the project toward short-term delivery (<1 year), with key milestones in September 2024 and June 2025. You will support software development activities as appropriate and participate in field experimentation of the common C2 solution.  TAS is headquartered in Brisbane, this is a Brisbane based position.  The role is scoped for a full-time applicant for 12 months, with potential for extension. The successful applicant will ultimately take on an expanded role across two other programmes due to commence in the next financial year, forming a core part of the growing TAS delivery team. This is an exciting opportunity to contribute during the early phases of a potentially significant expansion of TAS technical program.  Remuneration  Remuneration for this position is set at >$165,000 plus superannuation, dependent upon the experience of the successful applicant.  About You  You must have a results-driven and proactive approach to development. To meet rapid development timeframes, you must be comfortable working collaboratively, making prioritisation decisions, and communicating risk. You are familiar with, or willing to learn about, command and control concepts and technologies as they apply to autonomous systems, heterogeneous teams, and Defence activities.  You will demonstrate flexibility in your contribution to development and deployment efforts and must be capable of ready discussion with stakeholders to ensure delivery in accordance with expectations. You should have sufficient experience to support independent work and the ability to make informed decisions on behalf of the software team to achieve project objectives.  Essential Requirements  The following requirements are mandatory:  Experience in network architecture specification and implementation. Expert knowledge of Wireless WAN/LAN, Ethernet, VPNs and various network topologies. Experience with Linux-based operating systems and networks. Experience with rapid/agile development processes. Experience with hardware/software integration. Experience with software containerisation and deployment technologies including Docker Experience with third-party product integration. Experience with collaborative software development environments. Reside in Australia. Currently hold, or be eligible to hold, an AGSVA security clearance at NV1.  Desirable Requirements  The following requirements are desirable:  An understanding of command and control functions and architectures, relevant standards and protocols. Previous experience in a DevOps role Experience with acoustic communications. Familiarity with Defence experimentation or Defence operations. Proficiency in at least one compiled programming language, e.g. Go, Java or C++. Application  To apply, submit applications via the Seek job listing. Applications must include a cover letter addressing the selection criteria, a CV, and two current references by COB 17 August 2024  Questions can be directed to info@tasdcrc.com.au.

title: Analyst Cyber Security
description: Analyse security requirements and assess the needs within Customer groups so that a balance between business goals and risk mitigation
jobType: The successful candidate will analyse security requirements and assess the needs within Customer groups so that a balance between business goals and risk mitigation may be realised through the use of information security processes.  Role responsibilities:  Analyse, specify security requirements and specify or conduct technical security tests to ensure secure and resilient information systems, devices or applications are installed and maintained. Ensure that appropriate software and customer documentation is developed to support installed solutions and to ensure a smooth transition into the production environment. Ensure that proposed information security solutions are in accordance with the organisation's strategic information security direction and utilise the endorsed Corporate methodologies. Support the team leader in delivering information security advice and consulting services , ensuring at all times that a quality solution is being delivered within approved expenditure levels. Ability to deliver quality advice or services in at least one of the following information security fields: Performance, Governance, Policy, Strategy, Architecture, Training and Awareness, Communications, Incident Management, Vulnerability Management or Risk Build and maintain effective working relationships by communicating, consulting and negotiating with Information Management / Information Communication Technology professionals to promote sound Information Security practices throughout the Provide expert advice and support to the Director, Information Security and Manager, Information Security Solutions about information security matters. Demonstrated broad knowledge and understanding of the major trends, strategic directions and legislative and governance frameworks related to information security, with the capacity to successfully adopt them in the healthcare environment. Highly developed research, analytical, conceptual and problem solving skills including the proven capacity to initiate appropriate strategic and operational responses to key issues affecting the enterprise. Demonstrated highly developed interpersonal, presentation and consultation skills, with the ability to negotiate, influence and maintain effective relationships with senior and multi-disciplinary staff at the organisational, state and national levels. title: Engineering Manager (BE) - Content Platform (Remote across ANZ)
description: The Engineering Manager will be coaching two squads of ~4 engineers each, leaning heavily towards backend. They will be managing the team prioritie...
jobType: Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.  Hey, hello, hiya, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, , hallo, vtejte!  Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you're probably keen to find out what's on offer, so we'll get straight to the point.  Where and how you can work  Our flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. But you have choice in where and how you work. That means if you want to do your thing in the office (if you're near one), at home or a bit of both, it's up to you.  What youd be doing in this role  As Canva scales change continues to be part of our DNA. But we like to think that's all part of the fun. So this will give you the flavour of the type of things you'll be working on when you start, but this will likely evolve.  The Engineering Manager will be coaching two squads of ~4 engineers each, leaning heavily towards backend. They will be managing the team priorities, overseeing goal delivery and collaborating with other team leads. While coding will not be the main focus of this role, there can still be capacity for some hands-on work.  At the moment, this role is focused on:  Leading and coaching a motivated full stack team across two squads of up to 8 engineers and mentoringmembers of the team on technical approaches. Work with senior members of the team to guide the technical vision while being responsible for break-down and delivery of large projects Design, develop and deploy solutions and hands-on software development  working closely with leads, designers, and product managers Foster a impactful and healthy team via a healthy code review culture, knowledge sharing, design showcases, and process improvements Promote a safe and healthy culture with a focus on collaboration and open communication while advocating for engineering needs to non-technical stakeholders within the group Be accountable for the operation of services (including on-call support as part of the team roster, 1 week out of every 4-6 week)  You're probably a match if  Experience leading a team of software engineers building high-performing and collaborative teams. Experience owning and operating services with a healthy balance of delivery leadership, people leadership, and technical skills. Ability to lead by example; promote Canvas values, no-blame mentality, and engineering values. Experience working cross-functionally with Product Managers, Designers, and other business functions outside of engineering. Strong customer focus to understand the use cases and requirements of our internal customers. The requirement, although not he main part of the role, is still to be hands on in our backend tech stack - Java and AWS.   About the team  The public content library is one of the things differentiating Canva from its competition. The role of the Content Platform is to ingest content from external partners and creators, store and serve templates in an efficient way that meets Canvas scale and load and build the admin tools used by our operations team to maintain the state of the library. When it comes to templates, we also play a crucial role in making sure that templates support all the new features and doc types being launched. For example, whiteboards, docs, forms polls & quizzes + much more.  What's in it for you?  Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a stack of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.  Here's a taste of what's on offer:  Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally  Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.  Other stuff to know  We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.  Please note that interviews are conducted virtually.

title: Network and Security Lead
description: An exciting opportunity to join the AZZO Team!
jobType: Join us at AZZO, where we are committed to pioneering integrated technology for a sustainable future. As we continue to expand, we are seeking an enthusiastic and forward-thinking Network and Security lead to join our team. In this role, you will be integral to the design, implementation, and management of our clients' network infrastructure, operating within a combination of IT and OT environments.  If you're ready to make a meaningful impact and drive positive change, we want to hear from you. Join us in shaping the future of energy!  Key Responsibilities:  Design and implement network solutions by collaborating with stakeholders to create scalable, high-performance, and secure networks. Evaluate and enhance existing network infrastructure to improve performance, security, reliability, and cost efficiency. Implement and manage network security measures, including firewalls, VPNs, and intrusion detection systems, to ensure compliance with industry standards. Deploy network monitoring tools to maintain optimal network performance and minimize downtime. Work closely with various teams to understand business requirements and provide appropriate network solutions, while maintaining thorough documentation of network configurations and procedures. Stay informed on emerging technologies and trends in IT/OT networking and security and recommend improvements to enhance the organisations capabilities.  Qualifications & Experience:  5+ years working in a similar role and level. Experience in designing and implementing complex network solutions, with a strong grasp of network security principles and hands-on experience in implementing security measures across IT/OT networks. Proficiency with network monitoring tools, troubleshooting techniques, and working with Server & Desktop infrastructure technologies. Comprehensive understanding of networking protocols, hardware, and software in both on-premises and cloud-based environments.  What we offer:  On-site parking at state-of-the-art office facilities Competitive compensation package Enhanced parental leave Flexible working arrangements Opportunity to contribute meaningfully to the sustainable energy transition Training and development programs for both professional and personal development Inclusive working environment

These are permanent, ongoing positions at the APS 6 and Executive Level 1 classification levels.  The purpose of the Technology and Security Division is to secure, build, deliver and maintain ICT infrastructure and platforms in support of ABS mission of collecting, collating and disseminating official statistics to support decision making across Australias public and private sectors.  These roles will suit passionate ICT professionals wanting to contribute to the ongoing development, support and uplift of ABS technology solutions.  As a Data Engineer at the ABS you will have responsibility to build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources using Python/R/SQL/Apache Spark and AWS big data technologies. You will be required to work in partnership with ABS business areas and with suppliers to assemble complex ABS data, and to optimise data pipelines that meet business requirements.  To be considered for a Data Engineer position, you will need most, or all of the following skills, qualities and experience:  demonstrated experience building data pipelines and wrangling data experience in optimising data systems and the ability to assemble large, complex data sets that meet functional /non-functional business requirements a proven ability to work with multiple stakeholders as part of a multi-disciplinary agile team by fostering positive working relationships a proven ability to collaborate on IT design and IT best practice, security policies and guidelines, including clearly communicating technical concepts with technical and non-technical audiences a proven ability to apply DevOps practices and automation to the solution you are responsible for delivering demonstrated experience in public cloud platforms, services, and any of the following relevant products is highly desirable:  oCoding Languages (Python and/or R and/or SQL and/or Apache Spark)  oOrchestration and Automation (Lambda, Step Functions)  oDevOps Tools (Gitlab, AWS CodeCommit/Build/Deploy/Pipeline)  oETL tools (Informatica, Glue)  oInfrastructure as Code (CloudFormation, AWS Cloud Development Kit).  Executive Level 1 (EL 1) Application Developer  To be considered for an EL 1 Application Developer position you will need proven experience in some or all of the following:  significant applications development/data engineering experience technical leadership experience managing teams: this may include planning, tracking and reporting progress, and identifying and addressing impediments to ensure successful and on-time delivery of complex projects across multiple IT teams.  To be eligible to apply for these roles you must be an Australian citizen at the time you apply.  How to apply  To apply, complete an online application form on the ABS e-recruitment system. You will need to upload your current resume, provide referee details and respond to the following:  In 750 words or less, please provide an example that best demonstrates applying your Data Engineering or Application Development technical and/or leadership skills to deliver an IT solution that met business needs. Clearly articulate what your role and contribution was and the business benefits achieved, in the context of the selection criteria.  Note:  If you wish to be considered for more than one APS classification level you only need to submit one statement pitched at the EL 1 level.  We are also recruiting for Application Developers as part of this recruitment process.If you wish to apply for both the Application Developer and the Data Engineer roles you only need to submit one statement.  Applications close 11.30 p.m. (AEST) Wednesday 14th August 2024.

title: Senior Sourcing Manager - ICT Strategic Sourcing
description: Are you passionate about optimizing ICT procurement for NSW Government agencies? Join our Strategic Sourcing team at DCS!
jobType: Do you have a passion for achieving value for money and improving the ICT/digital procurement experience for both NSW Government agencies and suppliers?  The Department of Customer Service is looking for a Senior Sourcing Manager to join its Strategic Sourcing team!  Permanent ongoing clerk grade 11/12 opportunity   Flexible working arrangements   Reports to Director Strategic Sourcing    About you:  To be successful in this role, you will have:  a comprehensive understanding of government procurement requirements, policies and processes   a track record of delivering procurement processes in a complex stakeholder environment which have achieved favourable commercial outcomes   the ability to navigate and optimise complex procurement processes   the ability to coordinate procurement related inputs from stakeholders outside of your immediate organisation to realise solutions which are suitable for use by a broad range of customers and suppliers   a track record of acting according to the highest ethical standards   a sound understanding of the ICT market including knowledge of enterprise technologies commonly procured by large organisations   excellent written and verbal communication skills and   an ability to work as part of a team.    About the role:  We are looking for an energetic and process driven Senior Sourcing Manager to deliver procurement exercises required to establish and/or optimise all of government ICT agreements covering hardware, software, professional services, telecommunications and cloud. Your key accountabilities will include the following:  lead and manage procurement projects to deliver best value for money in procurement and sourcing activities adhering to Government processes, procedures, and priorities to meet stakeholder expectations and achieve organizational objectives   identify and manage commercial, contractual, operational, financial, reputational, ethical and supply chain risks to minimise negative impacts on sourcing objectives   provide expert, strategic advice to key customers and stakeholders on all aspects of procurement to encourage innovative practices and support the delivery of business and policy directions   contribute and support the development and implementation of best practice innovative solutions and procurement strategies to optimise value for money outcomes and meet business objectives   establish and maintain relationships with suppliers to identify and minimise risks and resolve issues to ensure that key performance indicators and service outcomes are achieved   lead the development of evidence-based procurement strategies, policies and processes to achieve quality and continuity of supply, procurement savings and improved business outcomes.    For further information, please see the Role Description. Where any inconsistency with the Role Description exists, this job advertisement will prevail.  Who we are:  The Department of Customer Service (DCS) is transforming the way NSW Government agencies interact with customers. We are passionate about putting the customer at the centre of everything we do and adopting new technologies to make government work better. DCS is a service provider and regulator, focusing on delivering first-class customer service, digital transformation, and regulatory reform to create better outcomes for the people of NSW. To find out more visit https://www.digital.nsw.gov.au/  Strategic Sourcing is a team of specialists within the ICT / Digital Sourcing branch of the Digital.NSW division. title: Senior Database Administrator
description: Elevate our digital landscape as a Senior Database Administrator, optimising ICT databases and enhancing reliability.
jobType: Job Reference: 1240005  Digital & Technology Solutions  Embark on an Exciting Tech Journey with Curtin University!  Are you passionate about technology, innovation, and driving change? Join us as we celebrate the successful completion of our digital transformation! Curtin University, a forward-thinking institution, is now leveraging major platforms like Amazon Web Services (AWS), Microsoft, and ServiceNow to deliver cutting-edge digital experiences for our students and staff. Your new role  As a Senior Database Administrator, you will play a crucial role in managing and optimising our ICT databases, ensuring high availability and reliability. This role overseas the general administration of databases and management of on premise and cloud-based applications, utilising platforms such as Oracle, Microsoft and AWS. This dynamic position offers you the opportunity to showcase your technical expertise, spearhead capacity planning initiatives and make a lasting impact on our digital landscape.  In this role you will:   Provide technical leadership in the specification of appropriate functional, technical, and system design specifications to meet the needs of business areas. Ensure high availability and performance of centrally managed ICT databases and services by diagnosing complex problems, tuning to improve performance, maintaining and supporting the underlying University-wide ICT infrastructure, including liaison with ICT hardware and software vendors where advanced diagnosis is required. Lead the planning and implementation of service continuity measures to ensure that business goals can be achieved even if a severe fault or serious incident occurs. Take a lead role in the planning of ongoing capacity improvements to databases to ensure that the technological infrastructure continues to provide the services required by the University. Protect the integrity of the ICT databases, servers and services by managing access, monitoring global ICT security news and technological developments, and acting on these using vendor advice and current technical knowledge. Define and comprehensively document technology implementation standards, protocols and processes related to implemented technologies. Key Requirements:  Extensive experience (5+ years) with enterprise-class Oracle RAC, AWS and Microsoft including capacity management. Proven experience in large-scale production environments. Strong organisational skills and experience in project management. Ability to lead and mentor team members. Advanced problem-solving skills and a commitment to client-focused service. Excellent communication skills. Knowledge of current and emerging technologies. Preferred Qualifications:  Experience with virtualised environments and cloud-based DB infrastructure. Certification in a relevant area or progress towards it. Experience with Oracle Application Server and Linux systems administration. Additional Information:  Must have current work rights in Australia matching the tenure of the role. Based in Perth, WA. Relocation and sponsorship support are not available. You may be required to work outside of office hours where necessary. Join us!  To apply, please provide your CV and a cover letter to allow us to assess your suitability for this role.  To view a copy of the Position Description, please copy and paste the following link into your web browser.  https://tinyurl.com/ymf2nebk  Applications close:10:15AM AWST Thursday 15 August 2024  About us  We are an energetic, dedicated team of academics and professionals working together to provide global solutions through quality graduates and innovative research. Curtin is a welcoming space where integrity, respect for one another, courage, excellence, and impact are essential to everyday life. Situated on Whadjuk Nyungar Country, our vibrant campus includes an art gallery, gym, childcare and medical centre, and endless food options including a supermarket.  We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people of diverse gender, sex and sexuality, people with disability and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.  For more information about our university, please visit www.curtin.edu.au  What we offer  Global Excellence:Curtin University proudly stands among the top one percent of global universities according to the ARWU 2023 rankings. Adaptable Work Environment:While our primary office is located at our Bentley Campus, we understand the importance of flexibility in today's work environment. Hybrid working arrangements are provided in accordance with business needs. Salary Packaging:Enjoy the perks of a generous superannuation contribution (17%) and customisable salary packaging benefits through Paywise. Competitive Leave Entitlements:Experience the added value of 17.5% Leave Loading, with the option to be paid out or taken as additional leave. Benefit from Parental Leave (26 weeks for the primary caregiver), Annual Leave (20 days), Personal Leave (14 days), Curtin University Leave (2 days), Study Leave, and Community Service Leave. Plus, access to Long Service Leave after 7 years of continuous service (65 days/13-week entitlement for full-time staff). Career and Development Opportunities:In line with our 2030 Strategic Plan, Curtin is committed to providing an inspiring, rewarding, and meaningful experience for our staff -empowering them to lead, innovate and strive for excellence. We provide staff with career and development opportunities, including access to various online and in-person training and info-sessions. Health and Wellness:Our on-campus Medical Centre prioritises Curtin staff and students. Join Curtin's Healthy Lifestyle Program, with up to 2 hours per week of paid time off to engage in University-approved healthy lifestyle activities. Explore Curtins wellbeing locations at https://tinyurl.com/mtyf3vad. title: Application Developer
description: Build and deliver contemporary solutions that will automate business processes and support optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data.
jobType: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to recruitApplication Developersto work in our Technology and Security Division. These are permanent, ongoing positions at the APS 6 and Executive Level 1 classification levels.  The purpose of the Technology and Security Division is to secure, build, deliver and maintain ICT infrastructure and platforms in support of ABS mission of collecting, collating and disseminating official statistics to support decision making across Australias public and private sectors.  These roles will suit passionate ICT professionals wanting to contribute to the ongoing development, support and uplift of ABS technology solutions.  As an Application Developer at the ABS you will have responsibility to build and deliver contemporary solutions that will automate business processes and support optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources.  To be considered for an Application Developer position, you will need most, or all of the following skills, qualities and experience:  demonstrated experience in developing software solutions to meet customer needs, by  ocreating and implementing the source code of new applications  otesting source code and debugging code  osupporting production applications and performing updates and modifications  a proven ability to work with multiple stakeholders as part of a multi-disciplinary agile team by fostering positive working relationships a proven ability to collaborate on IT design and IT best practice, security policies and guidelines, including clearly communicating technical concepts with technical and non-technical audiences a proven ability to apply DevOps practices and automation to the solution you are responsible for delivering demonstrated experience applying any of the following technologies is highly desirable:  oJava, JBoss, JSF, Spring Framework, Web technology (HTML, CSS, JavaScript), ReactJS, Python, Postgres, R, SQL, Oracle, PL/SQL  oAWS technologies: API Gateway, Lambda, S3, DynamoDB, RDS, ECS, CloudFormation, SageMaker  oWebservices and APIs (SOAP, REST and GraphQL)  oJIRA, Gitlab, AWS CodeCommit, Docker, Liquibase.  Executive Level 1 (EL 1) Application Developer  To be considered for an EL 1 Application Developer position you will need proven experience in some or all of the following:  significant applications development/data engineering experience technical leadership experience managing teams: this may include planning, tracking and reporting progress, and identifying and addressing impediments to ensure successful and on-time delivery of complex projects across multiple IT teams.  To be eligible to apply for these roles you must be an Australian citizen at the time you apply.  How to apply  To apply, complete an online application form on the ABS e-recruitment system. You will need to upload your current resume, provide referee details and respond to the following:  In 750 words or less, please provide an example that best demonstrates applying your Data Engineering or Application Development technical and/or leadership skills to deliver an IT solution that met business needs. Clearly articulate what your role and contribution was and the business benefits achieved, in the context of the selection criteria.  Note:  If you wish to be considered for more than one APS classification level you only need to submit one statement pitched at the EL 1 level.  We are also recruiting for Data Engineers as part of this recruitment process.If you wish to apply for both the Application Developer and the Data Engineer roles you only need to submit one statement.  Applications close 11.30 p.m. (AEST) Wednesday 14th August 2024.

title: Electronic Warfare Operator (No Experience)
description: Operate state-of-the-art technology and communications equipment to intercept and disrupt enemy transmissions in this highly classified role.
jobType: Your role: As an Electronic Warfare Operator, youll be trained to intercept and disrupt enemy communications and determine their threat level. Youll be part of an advanced close-knit team, the Signallers, who are dedicated to providing vital communications, information systems and electronic warfare support to the Army and wider Defence Force.  To kick off your career, following your initial training, youll be employed in a tactical unit, supporting infantry and armoured personnel as they train on exercises around the country. Here youll have the opportunity to work in a small team, receiving on-the-job mentoring and support. From there, you could specialise in:  Signals Analysis - analyse data and pass critical information to your commander  Electronic Attack - deny, disrupt and deceive enemy communications  Tactical Cyber Warfare - understand how networks, ICT and operating systems interact with each other in cyberspace  You will enjoy benefits including, but not limited to:  Free medical and dental, including access to allied health, rehabilitation, and mental health specialists  Competitive salary package with incremental salary increases as you gain experience Generous Superannuation of 16.4% - a huge 5.4% over the Australian standard A subsidised home loan or rent allowance Allowances and bonuses which recognise specialist skills and employment types  The ability to package your salary Job security Career progression and development Good work/life balance Travel opportunities Excellent social and fitness facilities Paid training    Location:  Following your initial military training, you could be posted to one of the many Army bases and units across Australia. The majority of these positions are located in QLD and the ACT.  Salary: In the Army you'll get paid a good salary from day one regardless of your age, experience or qualifications. Upon commencing training, your starting salary will be approximately $56,385 per annum plus 16.4% superannuation and your pay will increase as you progress through training.  On completion of your initial military training and initial employment training, you could earn $84,710 per annum plus generous super.  Apply now: For this role, you must be an Australian citizen, over 17 at the time of enlistment, and have completed an Australian Year 10 education (or equivalent) with passes in English and Mathematics. If you are not an Australian Citizen you may still be eligible to join the ADF if you meet certain criteria, please visit the ADF Careers Eligibility Page for more details.  You must also be able to successfully obtain a security clearance and meet the minimum medical and fitness requirements. Further information can be accessed via Army - Quick Eligibility Check (adfcareers.gov.au)  Click the APPLY button to start your journey to becoming an Army Electronic Warfare Operator and well get in contact with you shortly.  You can also visit the link below to view the full position description and learn more about life in the Army: Army - Electronic Warfare Operator (adfcareers.gov.au)

The role is responsible for establishing strategic objectives, driving process excellence providing process expertise and innovation, and enabling functional areas to lead their own programmes of continuous improvement whilst being guided by best practices.  This role is a full-time requirement, however Sandvik recognises the desire for flexible working options. Flexible employment arrangements include condensed working weeks, working from home, flexible start/finish times, etc.  Areas of responsibility (includes but not limited to);  Provide insight into how the business operates today and ensure that the requirements of service operations are known and considered in the design process Support the sales areas in the preparation and running of process, solution, and user experience. Take accountability for closing out business requirements related actions and decisions Work with operations managers, sales areas and system owners to ensure the designs being produced are in line with business expectations and meet their requirements Support the documentation of design artefacts and take overall ownership of the future business process model designs Support the project team in assessing business change impacts and engaging with the business teams to drive adoption  Your profile  To perform the job successfully, an individual should demonstrate the following competencies:  Tertiary qualification Business process analysis and process design, including documentation (flow diagrams, BPDs, etc.) Strong attention to detail System implementation experience Analytical mindset with excellent problem-solving capabilities Must be well organized, and able to meet deadlines Experience working with other Service Management Systems e.g. Maximo, Salesforce preferred  Agencies need not apply.  You must have the right to live and work in Australia to apply for this job and be willing to travel globally when required.  What we offer  A rewarding career with diverse opportunities Flexibility to work from home An Employee Benefits Program including salary sacrifice options 13% Superannuation on top of all earnings Company Performance Bonus scheme Length of Service Recognition program Company funded paid parental leave Training and development opportunities  Sandvik is proud to be a Work180 Endorsed Employer for Women. If you would like to know more information about how we are supporting our employees, you can view our policies and benefits on the Work180 website.  Talent Acquisition Specialist Monique King  0438 641 791

title: Software Developer/ Systems Administrator
description: AFP Digital Forensics are seeking experienced Software Developers to guide and develop the in-house development of Digital Forensic Software Tools.
jobType: Did you know?  The mission of the Australian Federal Police is to provide dynamic and effective law enforcement to the people of Australia. It provides policing throughout Australia in relation to the prevention and detection of crimes against the Commonwealth, its laws and integrity, and community police services to the Community of the ACT.  Working for the AFP provides you with a diverse and rewarding career. Whether you immerse yourself in a position on the frontline, or provide critical operational or professional support, the work you do makes a big impact on the people of Australia.  We recognise your contribution to our workforce and offer generous remuneration and conditions including:  Six weeks (30 days) of paid annual leave per year + additional paid Christmas stand down 4 extra mandatory leave rest days per year 18 days of paid personal leave per year Generous superannuation of 15.4% 16 weeks of paid maternity leave (after 12 months of service) + an additional 36 weeks of maternity leave without pay Generous salaries and incremental salary progression governed by the AFP Enterprise Agreement Flexible and hybrid working arrangement that provides work/life balance Health & wellbeing services  with a focus on early intervention, education and prevention. Access to ongoing training and professional development opportunities  What is the role?  Applications are sought from suitably qualified applicants wishing to be considered for the role of Senior Software Developer / Systems Administrator (Technical Specialist Framework - Level 3).  Digital Forensics Evidence Operations Network (EON) Support Team currently maintain and enhance capabilities utilised by Digital Forensic Examiners on a daily basis. Alongside the Chief Information Officer Command, the EON Support team also work to maintain and enhance the EON Environment, which holds and processes all Digital Forensic Evidence within the AFP.  The successful candidate will be working alongside Junior Software Developers, System Administrators and Digital Forensic Examiners. You will be the lead in driving the technical direction of Software Development and in-house developed capabilities pertaining to Digital Forensics. A Technical Specialist role does not hold any leadership or financial delegations.  You will also be required to contribute to the achievement of outcomes in accordance with the regulatory framework, the AFP Code of Conduct and the AFP Governance Instruments. It is expected that the successful applicant will deliver on the core responsibilities and meet any requirements of the position as outlined below.  What will you do?  Be the technical lead for enhancement and maintenance of in-house developed capabilities within Digital Forensics as created by other enabling areas of AFP Digital Forensics. Scope, develop and deliver new in-house capabilities that help support Digital Forensic teams. Drive DevOps practises within AFP Digital Forensics in regards to the enhancement and maintenance of existing and new in-house developed capabilities. Assist with the planning and maintenance of infrastructure to support in-house developed capabilities as well as daily Digital Forensic activities.  Essential Requirements  You must be an Australian Citizen at the time of application A Negative Vetting 1 (Secret) security clearance or the ability to obtain one Ability to plan, drive and deliver on multiple concurrent projects Conceptual and analytical skills Creative thinking Demonstrable relevant industry experience within the Information Technology Sector Demonstrable experience in Software Development Demonstrable experience in DevOps practises and their implementation Demonstrable experience in communicating technical requirements to non-technical management Demonstrable experience in working in small teams or individually on small-medium projects  Desirable Requirements  7+ years of professional experience in Software Development Relevant Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering or Information Technology Strong software development skills in multiple programming languages dealing with Front-end (React, Vue, JavaScript), Back-end (Python, Golang, Java) and Database (SQL, NoSQL) technologies Demonstrated ability to mentor and develop junior developers Experience in System Administration Passion for staying abreast of technology trends and introducing new ideas to the team  Additional Information  This position is an AFP Technical Specialist Band 3. This position offers ultimate flexibility in that you can work from anywhere in Australia including one of AFP's state offices or you can work completely remotely from home if you wish. Proof of a minimum of two COVID-19 vaccinations (or one dose if the Janssen vaccine was used) will be required if an offer of employment is made. Diversity and inclusion is an operational priority for the Australian Federal Police (AFP). To be an effective police force, we must be reflective of the community we serve, working across languages, cultures and transnational borders. The 2023-26 Diversity & Inclusion Strategy is the guiding framework for delivering the AFPs diversity and inclusion goals and reflecting our commitment to being an employer of choice, incorporating diversity and inclusion principles in day-to-day practice and building a psychologically and culturally safe workplace. This includes hiring people from diverse backgrounds who bring their lived experience to contribute, and add value, to the AFP. Find out more about how the AFP embraces diversity and inclusion.  Contacts and Closing Information  Contact Officer -Mark Shirbin,  Contact Officer Phone:02 5126 4457,  Contact Officer Email:Mark.Shirbin@afp.gov.au  Applications Close: 11:59pm (AEDT) 15/08/2024

title: Application Developer
description: Build and deliver contemporary solutions that will automate business processes and support optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data.
salary: Starting salary from $92K; package up to $150K
jobType: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to recruitApplication Developersto work in our Technology and Security Division. These are permanent, ongoing positions at the APS 6 and Executive Level 1 classification levels.  The purpose of the Technology and Security Division is to secure, build, deliver and maintain ICT infrastructure and platforms in support of ABS mission of collecting, collating and disseminating official statistics to support decision making across Australias public and private sectors.  These roles will suit passionate ICT professionals wanting to contribute to the ongoing development, support and uplift of ABS technology solutions.  As an Application Developer at the ABS you will have responsibility to build and deliver contemporary solutions that will automate business processes and support optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources.  To be considered for an Application Developer position, you will need most, or all of the following skills, qualities and experience:  demonstrated experience in developing software solutions to meet customer needs, by  ocreating and implementing the source code of new applications  otesting source code and debugging code  osupporting production applications and performing updates and modifications  a proven ability to work with multiple stakeholders as part of a multi-disciplinary agile team by fostering positive working relationships a proven ability to collaborate on IT design and IT best practice, security policies and guidelines, including clearly communicating technical concepts with technical and non-technical audiences a proven ability to apply DevOps practices and automation to the solution you are responsible for delivering demonstrated experience applying any of the following technologies is highly desirable:  oJava, JBoss, JSF, Spring Framework, Web technology (HTML, CSS, JavaScript), ReactJS, Python, Postgres, R, SQL, Oracle, PL/SQL  oAWS technologies: API Gateway, Lambda, S3, DynamoDB, RDS, ECS, CloudFormation, SageMaker  oWebservices and APIs (SOAP, REST and GraphQL)  oJIRA, Gitlab, AWS CodeCommit, Docker, Liquibase.  Executive Level 1 (EL 1) Application Developer  To be considered for an EL 1 Application Developer position you will need proven experience in some or all of the following:  significant applications development/data engineering experience technical leadership experience managing teams: this may include planning, tracking and reporting progress, and identifying and addressing impediments to ensure successful and on-time delivery of complex projects across multiple IT teams.  To be eligible to apply for these roles you must be an Australian citizen at the time you apply.  How to apply  To apply, complete an online application form on the ABS e-recruitment system. You will need to upload your current resume, provide referee details and respond to the following:  In 750 words or less, please provide an example that best demonstrates applying your Data Engineering or Application Development technical and/or leadership skills to deliver an IT solution that met business needs. Clearly articulate what your role and contribution was and the business benefits achieved, in the context of the selection criteria.  Note:  If you wish to be considered for more than one APS classification level you only need to submit one statement pitched at the EL 1 level.  We are also recruiting for Data Engineers as part of this recruitment process.If you wish to apply for both the Application Developer and the Data Engineer roles you only need to submit one statement.  Applications close 11.30 p.m. (AEST) Wednesday 14th August 2024.

title: Automation Test Analyst
description: Austrade is seeking an Automation Test Analyst
jobType: The Australian Trade and Investment CommissionAustradepromotes Australian trade,investment, tourism and education to the world. We deliver services to grow Australiaseconomic prosperity. Our purpose is to unlock opportunities that help Australian businesses go further, faster. Wehave a proud history of helping Australian businesses pursue their global ambitions throughour international expertise and trusted networks.  Were experts in connecting Australian businesses to the world and the world to Australianbusiness.  Our global network turns local market connections and insights into valuable export andinvestment support.     We contribute to Australias prosperity by:   linking Australian businesses to global export opportunities   providing market and industry insights, making it easier for businesses to go global   attracting international investment to drive local jobs and develop skills   leading policy and programs for Australian tourism and the visitor economy   attracting international students to study with Australia.     The Role:     The Digital Products and Platforms (DPP) Group is responsible for the delivery of the digital platform stack and strategy that underpins client and staff services at Austrade in conjunction with IT Services.  The EL1 Automation Test Analyst is part of the Test Services in the DPP branch and provides services to IT Services. They work closely with testers, business analysts, and developers in a multi-disciplinary team and contribute to the automation testing effort on our cloud platforms and applications.     The key duties of the position include:  Proactively contribute to all agile ceremonies (sprint planning, daily stand ups and retrospectives) for the projects assigned to,  Work closely with the project teams including developers and other testers to:  create and maintain automation test suites, test data and test scripts,  understand automation needs and identify opportunities for automated and performance testing,  Create, maintain, and execute re-usable automation test scripts to meet software release deliverables and project testing requirements,  Create, maintain, and execute re-usable release and upgrade automated regression test suites,  Identify and record defects for automated testing and manage them through to resolution,  Provide accurate reporting of problems identified during automation test execution and risks to the team leads/delivery managers,  Build and run the automated test scripts on Azure continuous integration (CI) pipelines and report automated test results,  Update automation test cases regularly to reflect any changes in the systems and applications,  Train new, junior and other manual testers to script and run the automated test scripts, when needed,  Perform manual testing as and when required, depending on project demands and priorities,  Build and maintain relationships with various stakeholders and communicate clearly and unambiguously with influence and confidence both verbally and in writing,  Report directly to the Director, Testing and perform duties assigned as and when required.  For more detailed information please see the Job Information Pack on the Austrade website.     Eligibility  Australian citizenship  our successful candidate must be an Australian citizen.  Security clearance  our successful candidate is required to hold, or have the ability to obtain, and maintain a Baseline security clearance.
