title: Technical Specialist (Dynamics 365 CE)
description: Implementing & contributing to design Dynamics 365 CE/Power Platform solutions for our customers
jobType: About Us  At Satalyst (A subsidiary of Canon Business Services), we specialise in Microsoft cloud solutions, modern applications, cyber security, data analytics, and business productivity tools and services. Our services cover the full customer lifecycle including consulting and advisory, software development and delivery, cloud infrastructure, cloud subscriptions, and ongoing technical support and optimisation services.  As a market leader in Business Process Optimisation and IT services for over 20 years, Canon Business Services ANZ helps organisations optimise, automate and transform their operations, setting them up for greater growth. We work collaboratively with customers to get the results they want, delivering bespoke solutions designed to meet and exceed their business needs, overcoming challenges, and freeing them up to focus on what sets them apart.  We're trusted by industry leaders because of our dedicated customer focus, and agile approaches to solving our clients' key challenges. With a commitment to delivering the best service management experience possible, many clients have partnered with us for more than a decade. The solutions we deliver are reliable, scalable, and cost-effective, helping customers to not just get ahead but stay ahead.  When you join Canon Business Services ANZ, you'll find a rewarding culture that values you. You'll be empowered to focus on your career progression and turn your goals into reality as an integral part of the group's success.     Be part of an organisation with Cloud First approach to Modern Applications Significant investment in your learning & career development Flexible work from home options Open to multiple locations, Perth & Adelaide preferred  About the Role  The objective of the Modern Applications practice is to become the trusted partner for our customers in advising and delivering modern application solutions. Alongside delivering solutions, the role would also involve supporting the sales team as the technical representative by attending / presenting at sales meetings, responding to tenders/RFPs. This is a hybrid role with flexible work from home options & may be based out of multiple locations within Australia. It reports to the Head of Modern Applications.  Main Duties  Implementing (hands on development) and contributing to design Power Platform/Dynamics 365 CE solutions following Microsoft's best practices. Participating in technical (code) reviews, technical documentation, and remediation plans throughout all aspects of the software development life cycle. Liaise closely with stakeholders and the wider project team in gathering requirements, agile ceremonies, user acceptance testing, and go live activities. Share/presenting to the wider Solutions team to share knowledge/experience in project implementations. Identify improvement opportunities as well as adopting new methods and best practices for CBS' clients Attend onsite visits to clients when required  About You  We are looking for someone who has experience in delivering Dynamics 365 CE/Power Platform solutions using Agile methodologies. They would demonstrate analytical, troubleshooting & problem-solving skills. Customer facing experience in consulting roles would be preferred. Certification in Dynamics 365 CE / Power Platform & experience in PCF development, scripting languages is highly desirable. Key skills include -  4+ years' development experience with Power Platform / Microsoft Dynamics 365 CE and its development tools 3+ years' development experience with Power Apps Portals/Power Pages and its development tools 3+ years' development experience with Power Automate Familiar and experience in two or more Dynamics 365 modules (Sales, Customer Service, Marketing, Project Service Automation/Project Operations, Field Services, etc.) Familiar and experience in Microsoft .NET, Visual Studio, XRM toolbox, Azure DevOps. Familiar and experience of SSRS reports and Power BI integration with Power Platform.  In return, we offer a supportive team environment where collaboration and support from your leaders and peers is the norm. We'll invest in your development and long-term future, and we can promise you a variety and enough challenge to keep things interesting across the wide variety of customer we support.  We believe in the power of an inclusive and diverse workforce. We trust you will bring your authentic self to work, and we will focus on making sure that together, we make a strong contribution to the broader community in which we operate. Where possible, flexible working arrangements are the norm, as we know a better work-life balance can improve your motivation, performance, and productivity.  Some Benefits include  Free onsite parking at Canon's offices (site dependent) Bonus Leave including: Birthday leave, to celebrate, relax or do something special Canon Day, an extra day of leave during the Christmas holidays Kyosei Day, or volunteer leave to take a paid day off to do good in your community Flexible working arrangements, where possible Training and development opportunities to help you bring your goals to life Wellbeing benefits, including everything from discounted health insurance to flu vaccines to confidential counselling Performance Recognition, in the form of quarterly and annual awards programs for high-performers Milestone recognition on your work anniversaries in the form of carbon credits, merchandise, or retirement fund rewards Discounted Canon products offered at discounted rates Education assistance to support the cost of any external training that gives you new skills for your job  As an equal opportunity employer focused on strengthening our inclusive culture, all applicants will be considered and we welcome applications from people of all ages, cultures including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, abilities, religious beliefs, national origin, sexual orientation and gender identities. Benefits/perks may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Canon Group and the country where you work. All applicants must be eligible to work in the country they are applying to at the time of application.  Looking to join this diverse team? Apply online now. Successful applicants will be notified of next steps.

title: Data Governance Manager
description: Great opportunity to work as Data Governance Manager within Baptcare!
jobType: Data Governance Manager  Full-time  Camberwell, VIC  About Us  At Baptcare, we care. Our Mission and Vision are lived through our WE CARE Values: for our residents, customers, clients, partners, and supporters; with the very young through to the very old, the vulnerable, with families through all of lifes stages and challenges.  Baptcare is a purpose driven organisation working across Victoria, Tasmania, and South Australia. Focused on providing residential and community care for older people and support to children, families, and people with disability, financially disadvantaged people and people seeking asylum.  Our Values areWellbeing,Ethics,Co-creating,Accountability,Respect andEffectiveness.   About the Role  The Data Governance Manager provides data governance expertise to business units and is responsible for overseeing and managing Baptcares data governance program. This role is the conduit between Baptcare management and employees or vendors in the application and adherence to the data governance framework and policies.  Key Responsibilities:  Oversee, provide leadership, and guide project teams to ensure data governance is applied to all projects. Develop and maintain business domain knowledge, data skills and awareness of data management and data governance practices, procedures, and trends. Offer expert knowledge and guidance on data governance best practices, policies, and procedures. Co-ordinate the data governance program Contribute to the creation of and implementation of Data Governance Framework and the delivery of roadmap initiatives. Ensure policies and plans are communicated and educate all business areas on data governance. Specify and co-ordinate data strategy metrics collection, auditing, and reporting processes, including to the Executive and Board where required. Identify and utilise opportunities for continuous data governance improvement. Provide data governance guidance on the management of risks associated with the use of data, including balancing security and privacy against the benefits of collecting and sharing data. Perform routine assessments or audits to identify improvement opportunities and action the.    About You:  Proven leadership experience in a data governance senior management role with a strong track record of successfully delivering complex projects and initiatives. Knowledge and experience of data governance frameworks (DAMA/DCAM), principles and methodologies. Experience with cloud-based data governance tools (e.g., Informatica, Alation, Collibra) A strong understanding of data management principles, including data quality, metadata management, and data lineage The ability to create and deliver training and awareness programs on data governance and data management best practices Strong communication skills with a proven history of influencing organisational data practices and policies Excellent communication and interpersonal skills for effective collaboration with senior management, technical and non- technical employees, and vendors Ability to build and maintain relationships with stakeholders and vendor    It is essential to have:    Bachelors degree in computer science, Information Systems, or a related field. 5+ years experience of successfully delivering complex Data Governance programs in a regulated environment. Certification in one or more data Governance methodologies (e.g., DAMA)    It is desirable that you have:    Relevant certifications in data governance Project Management Qualifications and / or experience Experience in Aged Care, Community Services or Not-for-Profit/NGO organisations.  For You  Baptcare is focused on living our values, not just talking about them. Youll find the culture at Baptcare is one of genuine respect, support, and positive intention. We work hard to achieve results through change, continuous improvement, and ongoing focus on providing the best service delivery to our stakeholders.  Further, the successful candidate will receive:  Work with a supportive and dynamic team. A competitive salary, plus access to the tax benefits of salary packaging and novated leasing. Career and development opportunities. Access to confidential counselling and support services. Be part of an organisation and a team that is driven to make a difference to the lives of our vulnerable community members.    How to Apply  Click'Apply Now'to submit your application.  Please submit as soon as possible as interviews will commence early!  Only short-listed applicants will be contacted.  Applicants must have the right to work in Australia. The successful applicant will be required to undergo a National Criminal History check.  If you require support with the application process, please contactgvenizelos@baptcare.org.au  At Baptcare, we value diversity in all forms and aim to co-create inclusive experiences and communities with our employees, volunteers, the people we work alongside and our partners. We are committed to diversity and inclusion across all we do and to building communities and workplaces where everyone belongs.  Baptcare is dedicated to the safety, empowerment, and participation of all children. We have zero tolerance of child abuse and are committed to a thoughtful, protective environment that supports infants, children, and young people to feel safe and respected.

title: People Applications Manager
description: Partner with People & Culture to unlock value and improve employee experiences from our applications suite globally, now and into the future.
jobType: About the role  Reporting to the Director of Platform and Integration, this newly created role in the Data, Digital, and Technology Function will have day-to-day technology ownership for all our employee applications, including Oracle HCM, Kronos WFD, CultureAmp, and integrations to key downstream systems, including Payroll. This position will work closely with Technology and our business partners in People & Culture to ensure that we can unlock value and improve employee experiences from our applications suite globally, now and into the future.  Provide leadership, guidance, and support to the People Application team, a small but dedicated team of technology professionals responsible for configuring and supporting all employee applications. Serve as the global subject matter expert on MyHR (Oracle HCM) and Kronos WFD. Support the business and technology to ensure our systems are configured, updated, and adopting new features and functionality. Maintain a strong global focus, recognising necessary differences while striving for process alignment wherever possible. Own and manage key vendor relationships, ensuring application costs are well controlled while maintaining interactive vendor and industry engagement. Lead the application platform team responsible for support, configuration changes, and minor and major enhancements through to project delivery. Drive continuous improvement in how we measure, manage, maintain, and enhance our technology platforms and consumer experiences. Champion a data-led approach and promote data analysis and insight for decision-making.  About you  We are seeking a technology expert in HR systems, with proven experience configuring and managing Oracles HCM system and/or Workforce Dimensions. You will have experience leading small to medium delivery teams as well as the ability to influence and collaborate with others globally.  Excellent communication skills and the ability to translate between Technology, People & Culture, and key stakeholders. Experience with HR systems management. Project management experience or certification is highly regarded, given the responsibility to manage medium-sized projects. Strong stakeholder management capability: able to achieve outcomes where there are multiple and varied points of view. Strong background in technology delivery and supporting digital transformation. Direct experience managing software and consulting budgets. Related professional qualifications and/or 7+ years of work experience.  Whats in it for you  AFR Boss Best Places to Work Top 10 Manufacturing and Consumer 2023 Access to the worlds most admired wines through our employee product allowance Flexible/hybrid environment to empower you to be your best Global opportunities across Australia & New Zealand, the US, Asia, UK/Europe Opportunity to build a career across multiple functions (were really good at doing this!) Structured development programs to support your health, wellbeing and career TWEforME Day  an additional day of leave each year, for you to do you Meeting-free Monday mornings (we all love this!)  Whats it like to work here?  We bring our whole selves, were courageous and we deliver together  thats our DNA.Were a passionate bunch who enjoy working together, like to have fun and keep things down-to-earth. Were brave enough and care enough to have the right conversations to get the best outcome and are famous for our can-do attitude.Were definitely glass half full people and see challenges as opportunities and move with pace to achieve our goals.  If youre ready to help us be the worlds most admired premium wine company, please apply now!  It takes all varietals!  Just like the wide range and variety of brands in our wine portfolio, TWE embraces diversity and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin or on the basis of disability. If you require any assistance to be included in our process, please contactrecruitment@tweglobal.com, quoting the job title and reference number.  How to apply  We move quickly at TWE and continually review applications, so if you dont want to miss out, apply today.  Please note that cover letters are not required (we really mean this!) All applicants will receive an email to invite them to complete online assessments that will cover three areas: personality profile, cultural fit and a cognitive assessment. The assessments should take around 30 minutes in total and you will be able to download a report at the end of it. We will then be in touch ASAP to update you on how your application is progressing. We ask you to try to complete the assessments ASAP  ideally within 24 to 48 hours.  Note that we prefer to deal with you directly; we havent briefed a recruitment agency on this role and wont be accepting CVs through any recruitment agency, so please apply directly.

title: Field Auditor
description: An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Field Auditor to join Service Stream in our Telecommunications team based in Brisbane.
jobType: Service Streams Telecommunications/ division are currently seeking a Field Auditor to join our growing company. You will be responsible for the key objectives of this position are to support the Senior Field Supervisor in the day-to-day operational activities and will be responsible for overall Regional Quality performance, Compliance and the continual improvement of the programs processes and operations within the NBN Unify Services contract. In addition, the Field Auditor will assist with internal and external stakeholder management, Quality Management through data capture and work type product quality auditing.  Nature of position:  Permanent, Full Time  Location: Brisbane South  Reporting Line:  Senior Field Supervisor    Key Responsibilities  This role is responsible for:  Implement and maintain the Quality Management Plan ensuring project compliance to AS/NZ ISO 9001:2008, and relevant legislative requirements. Support the regional delivery team in embedding the product quality assurance processes and systems within the operating environment. Provide product quality reporting and trend analysis to the Quality Project Lead Support field team with the closeout of all non-conformance issues with the regional delivery team. Ensure field Quality assurance activities are conducted in accordance with the audit schedule.  This role requires the Field Auditor to be aligned with Service Stream product quality auditing processes to a standard that will stand up to scrutiny by the client. The Field Auditor will achieve this outcome by using their skills, experience and specialist knowledge to coach and develop others via one on one coaching, development of training material, and courses and the delivery of same. The Field Auditor will be focused on continual improvement of product quality reporting and outcomes. This opportunity will suit a highly motivated and outcome driven individual who has a passion for delivering positive client outcomes, and a knack for effective stakeholder engagement.    About You  We are seeking an individual with demonstrated knowledge and experience with:  5 years Telecommunications Field based 3 years NBN Telecommunications FTTP, FTTC, FTTN, HFC and basic civils Intermediate level in Microsoft Office including Word, Excel, Power Point and Outlook  You will also demonstrate and possess the following:  Construction Industry White Card Provide First Aid Certificate - HLTAID003 Workzone Traffic Management - RIIWHS302D NBN Enable Accepted Accreditation    About Us  Service Stream, together with its subsidiaries and affiliates, is a leading national service provider to develop and operate Australia's essential communications, energy and water networks in the telecommunications, utilities and transport industries. We specialise in the design, construction and maintenance of new and existing networks, and deliver end-to-end engineering and asset management solutions on behalf of our blue-chip client base.  Service Stream is an equal opportunity employer who believes diversity of thought, background and experience strengthens relationships and benefits our people, clients, and communities. We are committed to cultivate an inclusive and high-performing culture where our people thrive and are proud to bring their whole selves to work, inspiring a respectful and inclusive environment. Service Stream encourages and welcomes the opportunity for applicants to share their lived experiences.  Service Stream does not accept any unsolicited resume referrals from external Recruitment or Labour Hire Companies

title: Optimisation Developer
description: Provide technical expertise in digital analytics best practices & implement digital analytics tracking solutions across Lotteries digital platforms.
jobType: Could this be one of those rare moments to do the best work of your career?  The Lottery Corporation is Australia's largest lottery company offering exciting games that deliver life-changing wins to customers and make a meaningful difference in the community.  We're the team who bring you Australia's favourite lottery games. For more than a century, we've been playing our role in making a better future by delivering winning moments every day to our people, our customers, retailers, partners and our community.  Share joy, spark possibilities and join the winning team today!  Provide technical expertise in digital analytics best practices & implement digital analytics tracking solutions across Lotteries digital platforms (website, iOS and Android).  What you'll do  Support the activation of the Lott's Digital Analytics implementation and Tag Management Solution involving ongoing delivery, maintenance and change management. Ensure digital data collected and passed into digital analytics platform is robust and accurate. Drive technical measurement and implementation needs to support digital experiments and personalisation initiatives. Write custom JavaScript & HTML mark up and governing 3rd party marketing tags within the TMS and Digital Analytics Configurations back ends. Support technical day to day operations of the Adobe Data Collection platform and technical configuration of Adobe Analytics. Support the Optimisation Manager to assess the feasibility of digital experiment designs. Create and implement digital experiments according to specifications across the Lott's Digital Channels.  What you'll bring  Hands-on experience in analytics implementation (Adobe or Google Analytics) from gathering requirements, solution design and technical implementation plus monitoring and debugging in both websites and app platforms Experience with Tag Management Solutions (GTM, Adobe Launch) to accurately configure the solutions to fulfill requirements, including eCommerce & custom tracking Experience in designing data layer requirements and data elements for custom tracking solutions (eCommerce, mobile screens, SPA's etc.) Technical experience in front-end development and applying it to digital analytics measurement Understanding of the current MarTech landscape and associated tools, platforms and practices. Knowledge of Testing/Opimisation tools (Adobe Target, VMO, AB Tasty etc.) and Website CMS's Working experience with repositories (GitHub, GitLab)    What you'll get  Not only will you receive an awesome candidate experience from our caring Talent team, the benefits of working with us are pretty good too!  The list is extensive but here are a few:  Join an amazing team who are ready to welcome you and set you up for success. Our people are warm, engaging and passionate. We love what we do and have fun along the way. Deliver extraordinary results while balancing work and life with our flex for great outcomes approach Find your balance with a variety of leave types such cultural leave, flexi-leave, volunteer leave, purchased leave and 18 weeks' parental leave for all new parents, regardless of gender or family type A true sense of belonging. We're committed to Inclusion & Diversity with a range of initiatives such as our Gender Affirmation Statement of Support, employee inclusion networks and diversity memberships Feel valued with experiences that are tailored to you, we'll always start from a 'yes' Support your health and wellbeing with our comprehensive (and free) app called to support you and your family's mental and physical health Make positive impacts with opportunities to volunteer with our community partners. We'll also dollar match fundraising efforts of our employees lending their support to registered charities Ignite your potential with our dedicated learning and development platform with resources from leadership to technology to support your bright future Maximise your home workspace with our home office reimbursement payment   About The Lottery Corporation The Lottery Corporation Limited (ASX: TLC) is Australia's leading lottery company with licences and approvals to operate in each Australian state and territory, except Western Australia.  Best known for The Lott and Keno, we're proudly one of the highest-performing lottery businesses in the world.  For more than a century, we've been supporting Australian communities through lottery taxes, donations, and partnerships. We play our role in making a better future by delivering winning moments every day to our people, our customers, retailers, partners, and our community.  Studies have shown that people from under-represented backgrounds are less likely to apply for roles where they don't match the job description criteria exactly. If this role is of interest to you and you're ready to spark possibilities with The Lottery Corporation, but don't feel that your experience aligns 100%, we would still love to hear from you and encourage you to apply.  We're committed to providing a safe, respectful and supportive work environment where our people feel included and rewarded. This commitment extends to our recruitment process. We encourage candidates to let us know if we can make any accommodations, so the process can be more user friendly for them.  We acknowledge and pay respect to the traditional custodians of the lands on which our offices, retail outlets and venues operate. We acknowledge the inextricable link First Peoples of Australia have with the land past, present and future.  Your online safety is important to us. We'll never request payment or credit card details from you to apply for a position at The Lottery Corporation. The most reliable source for available opportunities at The Lottery Corporation is our website. If you're uncertain whether a job ad is legitimate, do not provide your details. Verify via our website or contact our company.

title: Application Developer
description: Build and deliver contemporary solutions that will automate business processes and support optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data.
jobType: The Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) is looking to recruitApplication Developersto work in our Technology and Security Division. These are permanent, ongoing positions at the APS 6 and Executive Level 1 classification levels.  The purpose of the Technology and Security Division is to secure, build, deliver and maintain ICT infrastructure and platforms in support of ABS mission of collecting, collating and disseminating official statistics to support decision making across Australias public and private sectors.  These roles will suit passionate ICT professionals wanting to contribute to the ongoing development, support and uplift of ABS technology solutions.  As an Application Developer at the ABS you will have responsibility to build and deliver contemporary solutions that will automate business processes and support optimal extraction, transformation and loading of data from a wide variety of organisational data sources.  To be considered for an Application Developer position, you will need most, or all of the following skills, qualities and experience:  demonstrated experience in developing software solutions to meet customer needs, by  ocreating and implementing the source code of new applications  otesting source code and debugging code  osupporting production applications and performing updates and modifications  a proven ability to work with multiple stakeholders as part of a multi-disciplinary agile team by fostering positive working relationships a proven ability to collaborate on IT design and IT best practice, security policies and guidelines, including clearly communicating technical concepts with technical and non-technical audiences a proven ability to apply DevOps practices and automation to the solution you are responsible for delivering demonstrated experience applying any of the following technologies is highly desirable:  oJava, JBoss, JSF, Spring Framework, Web technology (HTML, CSS, JavaScript), ReactJS, Python, Postgres, R, SQL, Oracle, PL/SQL  oAWS technologies: API Gateway, Lambda, S3, DynamoDB, RDS, ECS, CloudFormation, SageMaker  oWebservices and APIs (SOAP, REST and GraphQL)  oJIRA, Gitlab, AWS CodeCommit, Docker, Liquibase.  Executive Level 1 (EL 1) Application Developer  To be considered for an EL 1 Application Developer position you will need proven experience in some or all of the following:  significant applications development/data engineering experience technical leadership experience managing teams: this may include planning, tracking and reporting progress, and identifying and addressing impediments to ensure successful and on-time delivery of complex projects across multiple IT teams.  To be eligible to apply for these roles you must be an Australian citizen at the time you apply.  How to apply  To apply, complete an online application form on the ABS e-recruitment system. You will need to upload your current resume, provide referee details and respond to the following:  In 750 words or less, please provide an example that best demonstrates applying your Data Engineering or Application Development technical and/or leadership skills to deliver an IT solution that met business needs. Clearly articulate what your role and contribution was and the business benefits achieved, in the context of the selection criteria.  Note:  If you wish to be considered for more than one APS classification level you only need to submit one statement pitched at the EL 1 level.  We are also recruiting for Data Engineers as part of this recruitment process.If you wish to apply for both the Application Developer and the Data Engineer roles you only need to submit one statement.  Applications close 11.30 p.m. (AEST) Wednesday 14th August 2024.

title: Change Manager
description: Reporting to the Head of Enterprise Change, the Change Manager will collaborate with key stakeholders to drive Change Management best practices.
jobType: VicRoads Registration and Licensing Services (RLS) has undergone a major organisational transformation and now, as a corporate entity, is creating a stronger business model to deliver VicRoads' long-term strategy.  The outcome of this corporate transformation is greater investment in our people, systems and technologies which will not only deliver greater capability internally but enable the delivery of new digital products and services to enhance the experience for our customers, our partners, and the Victorian community.  You have an amazing opportunity to make a truly significant impact on our team, the wider business as well as our stakeholders during this exciting period of growth for the company.  Annual Salary Range: Up to VPS 6.2 Employment Type: Full Time Ongoing Usual Work Location: Melbourne CBD / Work from home (Hybrid)  About the Team  Reporting to the Head of Enterprise Change, the Change Manager will collaborate with key stakeholders to support and drive the development and implementation of change plans across VicRoads RLS. This role will develop strategies which ensure that all projects that impact the way work is effectively managed to ensure seamless integration across operating models and business processes.  About the Opportunity  Working across multiple programs, this is the perfect opportunity for a technically focused change professional to make a significant impact at VicRoads during a period of rapid change. The role will be fast paced, working closely with our Program and Technology teams as well as Executive Leadership to develop and implement a change strategy for this multi-faceted program. Day-to-day you will be required to apply your advanced problem-solving skills, lead research and analysis into processes and training, and provide expert advice to your key stakeholders to drive implementation of change plans across the business.  About you  We are looking for someone who is highly collaborative, resilient and a true team player to gel with our close-knit group. A passionate self-motivator, you will bring a wealth of experience in implementing change, and a track-record of successfully delivering technology programs.  In return you will be supported not only by a positive and welcoming team, but a manager who leads by example, always puts you first and actively looks for ways to improve how we do things.  The following skills and experience will set you apart for this position:  Exercises independent judgement in the planning of and scheduling of activities required to implement a reasonably complex change plan. Demonstrates expert knowledge and understanding of the diverse range of responses to change and is flexible enough to work with a variety of individual needs and emotional stages. Leads the development and delivery of change strategies and interventions to support business efficiencies and improvement. Develops and manages changes to guidelines, standards, and work instructions to ensure quality and compliance outcomes are adhered to and benefits of planned product and service changes are achieved. Apply well developed specialist skills to anticipate barriers to success and develop change and business readiness plans to minimise risks and impacts and maximise stakeholder and business commitment prior to implementation. Effectively lead and manage the development and implementation of initiatives to improve employee and stakeholder engagement to achieve business outcomes. Proven ability to identify, manage and address risks and issues, including change resistance, with the potential to impact the successful implementation of transformation or change initiative. A valid driver's licence.  If you are looking for your next challenge somewhere you can make an impact and work alongside like-minded individuals, don't hesitate - apply now!  We can't wait to hear from you!  Culture:  To attract, retain and develop talented people, we provide genuine flexibility, a culture that supports people to be their best and on top of that - great opportunities for career development. We embrace diversity and inclusion and are proud our workforce reflects the community we serve.  What we offer:  Competitive salary and benefits Supportive, diverse, and inclusive work environment Opportunities for professional and personal development Flexible working arrangements and family friendly practices  How to Apply  Please submit your application via the "Apply" button. Applications should include a resume and a brief covering letter. Applications close 11.59pm on Wednesday 7th August.  For a copy of the Position Description please email talentacquisition@roads.vic.gov.au.  Unfortunately, applications cannot be accepted via this email.  Unfortunately, applications cannot be accepted via this email.  Please note: This position requires the successful employee to provide evidence of being fully vaccinated against COVID-19, or medical evidence which confirms the individual is unable to receive a dose, or a further dose, of a COVID-19 vaccine due to a medical contraindication or an acute medical illness.  Failure to comply with this condition of employment will impact your eligibility for employment in this position with Vic Roads. VicRoads is required to evidence your right to work in Australia and may ask for your consent to check records maintained by the Department of Immigration and Border Protection as well as records maintained by Victoria Police and VicRoads as part of the selection process. Information provided to VicRoads will be treated in the strictest confidence.

And we're counting on your unique voice and perspective to help EY become even better, too. Join us and build an exceptional experience for yourself, and a better working world for all. title: Platform Operations Engineer
description: Join a leading Payments company and be at the forefront of maintaining and enhancing the reliability of our production applications and services.
jobType: About Us    Through local expertise and global scale, we at Global Payments Oceania deliver market-leading technology solutions through five regional sub-brands  Eway, Ezidebit, Sentral, Pigeonhole Software and Storman.  Collectively, these brands are anchored by Global Payments, a world leader in payments and software solutions and a Fortune 500 brand with a worldwide footprint to accelerate our customers' full potential.   As pioneers within the Australia and New Zealand payments landscape,Ewayis a leading business-to-business ecommerce provider andEzidebita digital recurring business-to-consumer payments.    The Role    As a Platform Operations Engineer, you will be at the forefront of maintaining and enhancing the reliability of our production applications and services, particularly focusing on acquiring and scheme-related transactional support activities. You'll work within AWS infrastructure, supporting multiple technology stacks to ensure high availability, low latency, and exceptional performance of our payment systems.    Additionally you will be responsible for:    Developing a deep understanding of our clients, applications, and infrastructure to provide effective support and maintain system stability; Resolving integration issues, support API services, and troubleshoot production/project issues while adhering to ITIL framework procedures; Utilising tools like CloudWatch and New Relic to build, operate, and maintain system and application monitoring and health checks.; Maintaining PCI DSS compliance and assist with annual audits, ensuring our payment systems' security and integrity; Act as the first responder to critical alerts and incidents, collaborating with Incident Managers for swift resolution of major issues; Document and enhance existing processes, providing training and support to other analysts for knowledge transfer and supportability of new products; Keep clients and internal teams informed of issue resolutions and software releases, fostering strong working relationships with technical stakeholders.    About you    Global Payments is committed to Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (DE&I), with our vision to be Champions of Inclusion. We are looking for a teammate who believes in this vision, engages in our collective culture and strives to understand our customers, their needs and solutions that contribute to their success. A team mate that collaborates, partners and can stand with us. Other benefits available includesalary sacrifice,study leaveand anEmployee Stock Purchase Plan.    Ready to Apply? title: Platform Manager - Telephony & Agent Experience
description: Lead our contact center transformation by optimizing Amazon Connect for peak agent experience.
jobType: Let's talk about who we are  The nib Group has a mission and vision of people enjoying better health. Through our success, we aspire to more prosperous and sustainable communities, not only the creation of enterprise value. nib is a trusted health partner, helping members and travellers make more informed healthcare decisions, transact with healthcare systems and generally live healthier lives. Let's talk about this role  As the Platform Manager - Telephony & Agent Experience, you will be responsible for overseeing and optimising the contact centre technology platform (Amazon Connect) to enhance call centre agent performance and overall customer experience. Some other key responsibilities of the role include:  Leading initiatives to streamline and enhance the contact centre technology ecosystem, leveraging your strong technical expertise and business acumen to implement solutions.  Playing a pivotal role in aligning technology strategies with business objectives and ensuring the platform supports evolving needs of the contact centre.  Acting as the primary point of contact for telephony and agent experience, collaborating closely with IT, operations and business stakeholders to identify opportunities for improvement.  Providing thought leadership on contact centre best practices, whilst fostering a culture of continuous improvement within the team.   Let's talk about you  With previous experience managing contact centre telephony systems and technology platforms (e.g., Amazon Connect), other key skills and experience that will set you up for success in this role include:  Proven experience in enhancing call centre agent tools and workflows.  Strong background in product and platform management, with a focus on strategic alignment and value maximisation.  Experience with telephony technologies and integration with other systems.  Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to navigate complex technical environments.  Strong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively with technical and non-technical stakeholders.  Track record of delivering high-quality, reliable technology solutions in a contact centre environment.  Commitment to continuous improvement and staying current with industry best practices.  Experience with data analytics and leveraging data to drive strategic decisions.  Experience driving automation initiatives within a contact centre environment.    At nib, we recognise that some people may only apply when their education, skills and/or experiences are identical to what an employer is looking for in a candidate. Other benefits to support you at work (and play) include:  Generous discounts on nib health and travel insurance products including 50% discount on employee health insurance  The opportunity to give back to the community through paid leave for volunteering through nib Foundation  Support your better health - whatever that looks for you - through our nib Well Program and corporate fitness discounts  Access to our employee share plans, short-term incentive program and life and salary continuance insurance benefits  Benefits to support our diverse workforce with 18 weeks paid parental leave for all new parents regardless of carer status, 5 days paid cultural leave for First Nations peoples and 4 weeks paid gender affirmation leave for trans, gender diverse and intersex employees    The fine print  All your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines. Successful applicants will be required to complete a background check (including criminal history and bankruptcy check) prior to commencement of employment. title: Enterprise Digital Specialist - Security
description: You will drive the day-to-day execution of Microsoft's strategic business priorities  selling best-in-class cloud services.
jobType: Overview  Digital Sales Enterprise, part of Microsoft's SMC and Digital Sales organization, empowers our customers through the unique value of the Microsoft Cloud by building a globally led, digital-first scale organization aligned with partners. As part of our local subsidiaries or Digital Sales centers around the world, you will engage a dedicated set of enterprise customers to identify and achieve their business objectives through best-in-class digital engagement and partner co-selling. You will also have an opportunity to work collaboratively across teams while living our shared SMC and Digital Sales Culture priorities: Diversity and Inclusivity, Wellbeing, Sustainability, and Customer Obsession. If you have a passion for driving digital first solutions and delivering customer satisfaction, we invite you to learn more about Enterprise Digital Sales and the value we bring to our customers, partners, and one another, every day.  The Digital Cloud Acquisition team drives growth for Microsoft by helping customers realize the value of the Microsoft Cloud. Powered by a world-class connected sales and marketing platform, this team leverages marketing insights to reach customers when and where they want to engage digitally to help solve their business problems. Were powered by the latest innovations in Microsoft Dynamics 365 to engage with customers, collaborate across our global teams, and acquire and retain new business for Microsoft.   We are looking for an Enterprise Digital Specialist, specialising in Security solutions, who will work with our most important customers within our enterprise organization. You will drive the day-to-day execution of Microsoft's strategic business priorities  selling best-in-class cloud services and platforms to our managed customers and building digital transformation momentum for our customers, partners, and Microsoft.    Microsoft continues to invest in cybersecurity and research, to provide our customers with solutions that secure devices, identities, apps, cloudsthe fundamental fabric of our customers liveswith the full scale of our comprehensive multi-cloud, multiplatform solutions.   This role is flexible in that you can work up to 50% from home. If you are a strong team player, if you have an entrepreneurial spirit, if you are looking to build your sales experience, deliver outcomes for enterprise customers and if you are interested in joining a creative and inclusive global sales team, this is the role for you. We are looking for strong communicators and collaborators, for motivated individuals who are eager to learn, grow and make an impact and for sellers who are interested in being part of the next wave of connected sales and marketing innovation inside Microsoft.  Qualifications  There will be many opportunities for you to learn and grow into this role and Microsoft.  Required/Minimum Qualifications - 6+ years sales and negotiation experience; OR bachelors degree in business management, Information Technology, Marketing (or equivalent) or related field - AND 3+ years sales and negotiation experience or related work or internship experience.  Additional or Preferred Qualifications - 6+ years sales and negotiation experience; OR bachelors degree in business management, Information Technology, Marketing (or equivalent) or related field AND 4+ years sales and negotiation experience or related work or internship experience; OR masters degree in business management, Information Technology, Marketing (or equivalent) AND 1+ years sales and negotiation experience or related work. - 2-5+ years experience selling cloud services to large/global customers.  Proven self-starters able to work towards delivery of goals as best practices are being developed. Strong presentation, written, and verbal communication skills. Understanding partner ecosystems and the ability to leverage partner solutions/services to solve customer needs. Knowledge of enterprise software solutions and cloud platform competitor landscape. Demonstrate the business value of Microsoft's solutions with an understanding of Microsoft's strategies and products relative to major Microsoft competitors. Ability to maintain a high level of productivity, manage competing priorities and work effectively with high levels of autonomy and self-direction in a fast-paced, collaborative, and dynamic teaming environment. Experience in building and maintaining Executive level (CXO) stakeholder relationships and leading value proposition conversations aligned to customer priorities and outcomes.   Your exceptional sales skills, deep understanding of enterprise needs, and ability to build strong customer relationships will be instrumental in achieving sales targets and driving customer success.   Microsoft believes that by investing in our people and creating an inclusive environment, our team will do their best work. See our complete list of benefits and why we are recognised as an Endorsed Employer for Women by WORK180. Microsoft Benefits | WORK180 Endorsed Employer  Our mission is deeply inclusive. Inside Microsoft | Global Diversity and Inclusion at Microsoft  What next?  Even if you feel you may not meet 100% of the criteria, please apply. You may exceed your own expectations, or we may have another opportunity that suits your potential. While were not able to reach out directly to every applicant, we will always do our best to help you feel heard and supported throughout the experience.   Responsibilities  As a Security Digital Specialist, you will play a vital role in driving business growth by generating new leads, engaging with prospective clients, and building strong relationships. You will receive comprehensive training and mentorship to develop your sales skills and gain a deep understanding of Microsoft products and solutions.  Customer First Mindset - Engage with and enable our customers and key decision-makers, delivering a connected customer engagement experience and driving customer satisfaction through digital sales excellence, empowered by world-class data, marketing systems and platforms.  Meet operational standards and maintain reporting accuracy for key metrics  including response rates, prospecting activity tracking, pipeline, conversion, velocity, and accuracy. Adopt program processes, procedures, and tools to provide accurate on-time reporting that maximizes attainment of strategic goals and delivers competitive business insights, trends, and analysis.  Share best practices, learnings, and customer insights with stakeholder groups to elevate team capabilities and drive change based on insights.  Work in a fast-paced, collaborative, and dynamic teaming environment with field specialists, technical resources, and partner teams to effectively manage customer opportunities, deliver connected customer experiences, achieve customer outcomes with Microsoft's leading cloud technologies, and accelerate value across the customer lifecycle.  Effectively turn prospects and qualified digital leads into opportunities and revenue pipeline and engage with customers across industries, company sizes and types to determine their needs and identify opportunities to fulfill their needs with Microsoft's leading cloud technologies, with this role particularly focused on the specific solution area you are driving.  Stay motivated and maintain a positive approach to problem-solving, learning, and development in a rapidly growing business with evolving market conditions and customer needs.  Develop a strong understanding of your customers, their security challenges, and strategic business objectives to identify their core security needs and connect them with our Security solutions.  Engage with Partner(s) - Leverage and scale through aligning early with Global Partner Solutions (GPS) organisations prioritized partners.  Benefits/perks listed below may vary depending on the nature of your employment with Microsoft and the country where you work.  Industry leading healthcare Educational resources Discounts on products and services Savings and investments Maternity and paternity leave Generous time away Giving programs Opportunities to network and connect

title: ServiceNow ITOM Specialist

jobType: Join a dynamic and growing team  Support the delivery of the Bank's Technology Roadmap  Hybrid working arrangements available   Do work that makes a difference  Technology is an inherent part of enabling the Reserve Bank of Australia's policy and operational objectives. With the country depending upon our systems being secure, highly resilient and efficient, you will work within the Bank's Informational Technology (IT) Department and be at the forefront of progressing ServiceNow ITOM capabilities particularly in Discovery and Service Mapping helping to ensure the stability and availability of services that are critical to our organisation's success.   Your team  Within the Information Technology (IT) department, you will be part of the IT Service Management team as a ServiceNow ITOM Specialist actively working on the ServiceNow Platform, to transform and develop the core IT functions that support the Reserve Bank's policy, operational and corporate objectives.   Your background  We are seeking a talented and driven ServiceNow Service Mapping Administrator to:   Work closely with IT technical teams and business stakeholders to deliver on the ServiceNow Discovery and Service Mapping backlog/roadmap. Review and Maintain effective IT Operations Management (ITOM) schedules, and develop ITOM dashboards   To be successful in this critical role. you will:   Experience using ServiceNow, specifically Service Mapping and ServiceNow Discovery  ServiceNow scripting and API skills  Knowledge of CMDB principles and data mapping for accurate population.  Experience using the Common Source Data Model (CSDM) for Service Mapping.  Experience in ServiceNow ITOM Discovery  Demonstrated effective management of service/customer delivery experience.  Knowledge of best-practice service management principles and processes.  Experience in collaborating with business stakeholders and project managers to identify project objectives, requirements, scope and timeline estimation.  Exceptional interpersonal skills to collaborate, influence and partner effectively with key stakeholders across the Reserve Bank  Be an energetic strategic thinker who has considerable attention to detail.  Be More  The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operates infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people.  Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people have a meaningful role to play in achieving these objectives. We encourage intelligent inquiry, and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts.  We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the Bank forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.  The Reserve Bank of Australia is an equal opportunity employer. title: Software Developer/ Systems Administrator
description: AFP Digital Forensics are seeking experienced Software Developers to guide and develop the in-house development of Digital Forensic Software Tools.
jobType: Did you know?  The mission of the Australian Federal Police is to provide dynamic and effective law enforcement to the people of Australia. It provides policing throughout Australia in relation to the prevention and detection of crimes against the Commonwealth, its laws and integrity, and community police services to the Community of the ACT.  Working for the AFP provides you with a diverse and rewarding career. Whether you immerse yourself in a position on the frontline, or provide critical operational or professional support, the work you do makes a big impact on the people of Australia.  We recognise your contribution to our workforce and offer generous remuneration and conditions including:  Six weeks (30 days) of paid annual leave per year + additional paid Christmas stand down 4 extra mandatory leave rest days per year 18 days of paid personal leave per year Generous superannuation of 15.4% 16 weeks of paid maternity leave (after 12 months of service) + an additional 36 weeks of maternity leave without pay Generous salaries and incremental salary progression governed by the AFP Enterprise Agreement Flexible and hybrid working arrangement that provides work/life balance Health & wellbeing services  with a focus on early intervention, education and prevention. Access to ongoing training and professional development opportunities  What is the role?  Applications are sought from suitably qualified applicants wishing to be considered for the role of Senior Software Developer / Systems Administrator (Technical Specialist Framework - Level 3).  Digital Forensics Evidence Operations Network (EON) Support Team currently maintain and enhance capabilities utilised by Digital Forensic Examiners on a daily basis. Alongside the Chief Information Officer Command, the EON Support team also work to maintain and enhance the EON Environment, which holds and processes all Digital Forensic Evidence within the AFP.  The successful candidate will be working alongside Junior Software Developers, System Administrators and Digital Forensic Examiners. You will be the lead in driving the technical direction of Software Development and in-house developed capabilities pertaining to Digital Forensics. A Technical Specialist role does not hold any leadership or financial delegations.  You will also be required to contribute to the achievement of outcomes in accordance with the regulatory framework, the AFP Code of Conduct and the AFP Governance Instruments. It is expected that the successful applicant will deliver on the core responsibilities and meet any requirements of the position as outlined below.  What will you do?  Be the technical lead for enhancement and maintenance of in-house developed capabilities within Digital Forensics as created by other enabling areas of AFP Digital Forensics. Scope, develop and deliver new in-house capabilities that help support Digital Forensic teams. Drive DevOps practises within AFP Digital Forensics in regards to the enhancement and maintenance of existing and new in-house developed capabilities. Assist with the planning and maintenance of infrastructure to support in-house developed capabilities as well as daily Digital Forensic activities.  Essential Requirements  You must be an Australian Citizen at the time of application A Negative Vetting 1 (Secret) security clearance or the ability to obtain one Ability to plan, drive and deliver on multiple concurrent projects Conceptual and analytical skills Creative thinking Demonstrable relevant industry experience within the Information Technology Sector Demonstrable experience in Software Development Demonstrable experience in DevOps practises and their implementation Demonstrable experience in communicating technical requirements to non-technical management Demonstrable experience in working in small teams or individually on small-medium projects  Desirable Requirements  7+ years of professional experience in Software Development Relevant Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering or Information Technology Strong software development skills in multiple programming languages dealing with Front-end (React, Vue, JavaScript), Back-end (Python, Golang, Java) and Database (SQL, NoSQL) technologies Demonstrated ability to mentor and develop junior developers Experience in System Administration Passion for staying abreast of technology trends and introducing new ideas to the team  Additional Information  This position is an AFP Technical Specialist Band 3. This position offers ultimate flexibility in that you can work from anywhere in Australia including one of AFP's state offices or you can work completely remotely from home if you wish. Proof of a minimum of two COVID-19 vaccinations (or one dose if the Janssen vaccine was used) will be required if an offer of employment is made. Diversity and inclusion is an operational priority for the Australian Federal Police (AFP). To be an effective police force, we must be reflective of the community we serve, working across languages, cultures and transnational borders. The 2023-26 Diversity & Inclusion Strategy is the guiding framework for delivering the AFPs diversity and inclusion goals and reflecting our commitment to being an employer of choice, incorporating diversity and inclusion principles in day-to-day practice and building a psychologically and culturally safe workplace. This includes hiring people from diverse backgrounds who bring their lived experience to contribute, and add value, to the AFP. Find out more about how the AFP embraces diversity and inclusion.  Contacts and Closing Information  Contact Officer -Mark Shirbin,  Contact Officer Phone:02 5126 4457,  Contact Officer Email:Mark.Shirbin@afp.gov.au  Applications Close: 11:59pm (AEDT) 15/08/2024

title: Software Developer/ Systems Administrator
description: AFP Digital Forensics are seeking experienced Software Developers to guide and develop the in-house development of Digital Forensic Software Tools.
jobType: Did you know?  The mission of the Australian Federal Police is to provide dynamic and effective law enforcement to the people of Australia. It provides policing throughout Australia in relation to the prevention and detection of crimes against the Commonwealth, its laws and integrity, and community police services to the Community of the ACT.  Working for the AFP provides you with a diverse and rewarding career. Whether you immerse yourself in a position on the frontline, or provide critical operational or professional support, the work you do makes a big impact on the people of Australia.  We recognise your contribution to our workforce and offer generous remuneration and conditions including:  Six weeks (30 days) of paid annual leave per year + additional paid Christmas stand down 4 extra mandatory leave rest days per year 18 days of paid personal leave per year Generous superannuation of 15.4% 16 weeks of paid maternity leave (after 12 months of service) + an additional 36 weeks of maternity leave without pay Generous salaries and incremental salary progression governed by the AFP Enterprise Agreement Flexible and hybrid working arrangement that provides work/life balance Health & wellbeing services  with a focus on early intervention, education and prevention. Access to ongoing training and professional development opportunities  What is the role?  Applications are sought from suitably qualified applicants wishing to be considered for the role of Senior Software Developer / Systems Administrator (Technical Specialist Framework - Level 3).  Digital Forensics Evidence Operations Network (EON) Support Team currently maintain and enhance capabilities utilised by Digital Forensic Examiners on a daily basis. Alongside the Chief Information Officer Command, the EON Support team also work to maintain and enhance the EON Environment, which holds and processes all Digital Forensic Evidence within the AFP.  The successful candidate will be working alongside Junior Software Developers, System Administrators and Digital Forensic Examiners. You will be the lead in driving the technical direction of Software Development and in-house developed capabilities pertaining to Digital Forensics. A Technical Specialist role does not hold any leadership or financial delegations.  You will also be required to contribute to the achievement of outcomes in accordance with the regulatory framework, the AFP Code of Conduct and the AFP Governance Instruments. It is expected that the successful applicant will deliver on the core responsibilities and meet any requirements of the position as outlined below.  What will you do?  Be the technical lead for enhancement and maintenance of in-house developed capabilities within Digital Forensics as created by other enabling areas of AFP Digital Forensics. Scope, develop and deliver new in-house capabilities that help support Digital Forensic teams. Drive DevOps practises within AFP Digital Forensics in regards to the enhancement and maintenance of existing and new in-house developed capabilities. Assist with the planning and maintenance of infrastructure to support in-house developed capabilities as well as daily Digital Forensic activities.  Essential Requirements  You must be an Australian Citizen at the time of application A Negative Vetting 1 (Secret) security clearance or the ability to obtain one Ability to plan, drive and deliver on multiple concurrent projects Conceptual and analytical skills Creative thinking Demonstrable relevant industry experience within the Information Technology Sector Demonstrable experience in Software Development Demonstrable experience in DevOps practises and their implementation Demonstrable experience in communicating technical requirements to non-technical management Demonstrable experience in working in small teams or individually on small-medium projects  Desirable Requirements  7+ years of professional experience in Software Development Relevant Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering or Information Technology Strong software development skills in multiple programming languages dealing with Front-end (React, Vue, JavaScript), Back-end (Python, Golang, Java) and Database (SQL, NoSQL) technologies Demonstrated ability to mentor and develop junior developers Experience in System Administration Passion for staying abreast of technology trends and introducing new ideas to the team  Additional Information  This position is an AFP Technical Specialist Band 3. This position offers ultimate flexibility in that you can work from anywhere in Australia including one of AFP's state offices or you can work completely remotely from home if you wish. Proof of a minimum of two COVID-19 vaccinations (or one dose if the Janssen vaccine was used) will be required if an offer of employment is made. Diversity and inclusion is an operational priority for the Australian Federal Police (AFP). To be an effective police force, we must be reflective of the community we serve, working across languages, cultures and transnational borders. The 2023-26 Diversity & Inclusion Strategy is the guiding framework for delivering the AFPs diversity and inclusion goals and reflecting our commitment to being an employer of choice, incorporating diversity and inclusion principles in day-to-day practice and building a psychologically and culturally safe workplace. This includes hiring people from diverse backgrounds who bring their lived experience to contribute, and add value, to the AFP. Find out more about how the AFP embraces diversity and inclusion.  Contacts and Closing Information  Contact Officer -Mark Shirbin,  Contact Officer Phone:02 5126 4457,  Contact Officer Email:Mark.Shirbin@afp.gov.au  Applications Close: 11:59pm (AEDT) 15/08/2024

title: Modern Workplace Functional Analyst
description: Drive the Linfox Business Strategy in support of Microsoft 365 (M365) platforms required by our operations and corporate shared services functions.
jobType: Here at Linfox, we believe together, anything is possible. Use sophisticated technology to deliver everyday essentials and natural resources for Australias biggest companies. Work with major customers in retail, healthcare, government, and defence. Shape the future of logistics with industry leading innovations in safety, sustainability, and efficiency. Create a career to be proud of. Expect all this and more when you join Linfox.  What does the job look like?  The Modern Workplace Functional Analyst (MWFA) supports the Microsoft 365 (M365) platforms required by Linfox operations and Corporate shared services functions, to drive the Linfox Business Strategy. The MWFA plays a key role in building adoption of the Microsoft 365 platform, building solutions with the toolsets and providing support to all end-users across Linfox. Key areas:  Provide support to all end-users for the following areas: Existing solutions which have been developed within the platform. Providing new user support for basic training Troubleshooting issues that have occurred on the platform and escalating to Productivity Systems Manager, other areas within ADIT, or to the vendor by raising a ticket with Microsoft Premier Support Design and drive Modern Workplace areas towards a desirable future state: Participate in strategic planning for the M365 platforms through roadmap design and advising areas where new features will benefit the user base. Engaging with Microsoft, partners, and community groups to be informed and across the newest feature rollouts and changes to the platform. Ensure promotion of M365 platforms as Linfoxs preferred platform for productivity and leveraged as appropriate, while collaborating with ADIT teams to architect fit-for-purpose processes and solutions. Ensure capability that is planned is supportable, re-usable, repeatable, and predictable in time cost and quality. This role requires a self-starter who is action orientated set on meeting challenging objectives and initiates actions with a commitment to clear outcomes. Demonstrated experience in providing solutions using functionality from M365 toolsets including SharePoint, PowerApps, Power Automate (Flow), Dynamics, Teams, and others Experience training end-users and providing support. Desired experience participating and involvement in digital transformation adoption or change management and the ability to work effectively with both internal and external stakeholders, as well as proven track record to influence stakeholders, without having direct authority.  At Linfox, we are passionate about creating an inclusive workplace where people can perform at their best. We welcome and encourage applications from people of all backgrounds and cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), ages, religions, abilities, gender identities and sexual orientations.  Sound like you? Please click the apply button to submit your application and resume.  We kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. Linfox is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.  Further information  You will be required to meet Linfox's employment criteria which will include but not be limited to a criminal history check and full medical with a drug and alcohol test. title: Software Architect

jobType: About the Role:  TheSoftware Architectensures that the underlying architecture supports both functional and non-functional requirements and that the requirements align with the technical strategy and vision of the organisation.  To be considered for this role, you must be an Australian citizen.  As a Software Architect, your primary responsibilities include:  Take ownership and guide the implementation of technical solutions to meet client needs. Collaborate with clients, external organisations and internal engineering disciplines to ensure successful project outcomes. Create detailed technical and functional documentation, outlining the scope and design of solutions. Lead and drive internal projects to improve technical methodologies, contributing to the enhancement of our engineering discipline. Ensure engineering teams have the necessary tools and software to perform their duties effectively. Participate in reviewing and approving architecture decisions made by engineering teams. Strong knowledge in software engineering with extensive experience working with cross-functional teams in designing and delivering end-to-end software. Demonstrated ability to guide the implementation of technical solutions. Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to remove technical roadblocks for engineering teams. In-depth knowledge of coding and design best practices. Proven experience planning and facilitating workshops. Expertise in creating comprehensive technical and functional documentation. Understanding of engineering tools and software.  Desirable Knowledge and Skills:  Familiarity with Agile delivery methodologies (Scrum, SAFe or similar) Broad understanding of technologies in the developer ecosystem, including IDEs, developer frameworks, and multiple language stacks. Understanding of DevOps philosophy, practices, tools, and ways of securing DevOps processes (e.g., DevSecOps or Rugged DevOps). Proficiency in automation tools, infrastructure-as-code, and configuration-as-code. Knowledge of databases, containers, container orchestration, and container hardening. Eligibility requirements can be found at http://www.defence.gov.au/agsva  About the Company:  Consunet is headquartered in the Adelaide CBD with operations in Adelaide, Edinburgh (SA) and Canberra. We collaboratively work with customers to understand and solve complex problems. We develop world-leading solutions that deliver enduring benefits.  As a 100% Australian-owned and operated corporation, Consunet strives to be the countrys leading cyber and spectrum security solution developer, and trusted industry partner to the Australian Defence and cyber security communities. A strong research and development and collaboration emphasis underpins our culture of innovation and excellence. We lead with vision to deliver trusted and sustainable outcomes for discerning and astute customers.  To learn more about Consunet, please visit: www.consunet.com.au  Further benefits include:  A workplace that believes in innovation, quality, and a work-life balance. A flexible, inclusive, and friendly work environment. Competitive remuneration. Salary packaging options. Paid Parental Leave. Reserve Leave Generous Study Loan Scheme. Mentoring and support from our experienced team members.  To Apply:  Click Apply Now. Please attacha cover letter summarising your experience when applying.

title: Land Access Advisor
description: Ensure high-quality work by applying your comprehensive knowledge of Telecommunications land access legislation to the organisation's activities.
jobType: The Opportunity  Are you passionate about town planning, environmental sciences, and telecommunications? Do you thrive on ensuring statutory approvals and stakeholder engagements are meticulously managed? Utilise your knowledge of the Telecommunications Act 1997 and the Telecommunications Code of Practice, Supportive, friendly, and collaborative team environment, Access to the company Employee Assistance Program, Commitment to your ongoing professional development.
