title: Senior Consultant, Cybersecurity
description: FTI Consulting is the number one global expert firm for organisations facing crisis, transformation and moments of truth. The Cybersecurity Practic...
jobType: About The Role  FTI Consulting is the number one global expert firm for organisations facing crisis, transformation and moments of truth. The Cybersecurity Practice within FTI Consulting is a leading provider of independent cybersecurity and risk management advisory services with a core offering focused on (but not limited to) Cyber Readiness, Incident Response and Complex Investigations & Litigation Support. We are seeking to appoint a Senior Consultant to our cybersecurity practice. This is a full-time role offering excellent career opportunities and professional development for your future progression within the firm.  What Youll Do  Work with clients to provide strategic and tactical advice that enhance our clients cybersecurity posture: Development of cybersecurity strategies and roadmaps. Review and establish information security policy frameworks. Perform cybersecurity current state assessments, assessing the effectiveness of cybersecurity processes/controls and risks against best practice frameworks such as ISO27000 series, NIST CSF, AESCSF, E8 and other regulatory compliance frameworks. Contribute to establishing risk management plans, such as SOCI Critical Infrastructure Risk Management Program (CIRMP). Establish and support the delivery of cybersecurity risk management remediation roadmaps. Develop security awareness plans based on current and relevant cyber threats and risks. Perform threat modelling and risk assessments to identify security risks, vulnerabilities, and risk mitigation strategies. Conduct security architecture assessments assessing the completeness and effectiveness of security controls, identifying security control gaps, security weaknesses and potential attack vectors. Perform third-party security risk assessments and support the implementation of third-party risk management programs. Assist in the planning of client deliverables (i.e. security strategy, risk assessments, policies & standards, scope documents and reports). Participate in post incident reviews and post data breach related investigations, identifying and documenting the strategic and tactical root causes.  How Youll Grow  This is an excellent opportunity for a person with proven, hands-on cybersecurity experience to join a dynamic and growing cybersecurity team. With the ever-evolving cybersecurity landscape, the need for continuous professional development remains at the forefront of the quality of our team and is wholly supported.  We are committed to investing and supporting you in your professional development and we aim to promote continuous learning and individual skills development through on-the-job learning, self-guided professional development courses and certifications.  Qualifications & Experience  Tertiary qualifications in cybersecurity or similar technology discipline or agreed equivalent experience. Industry-recognized security certifications such as SABSA, CISSP, CISA, SANS or similar. Previous advisory and consulting experience in relation to cybersecurity engagements. Knowledge of cybersecurity and/or risk assessment standards and frameworks (NIST, ISO27001, APRA, ASD ISM, PCI-DSS). Demonstrated knowledge of cloud infrastructure security practices (AWS/Azure). 3-6+ years of cybersecurity experience preferrable with exposure to consulting-related activities. High-level written and spoken English language skills. The ability to work on multiple clients matters at one time. The ability at to work with limited supervision. A track record of collaborating effectively with other team members in time sensitive situations. A strong work ethic and integrity and high level of professionalism. Travel to FTI Consultings interstate and/or client locations as required.  Our Benefits  Apart from the well-structured career path and excellent team environment, our employees enjoy a variety of perks and benefits. Our benefits include, but are not limited to:  Attractive remuneration, including discretionary bonuses available to all employees 18 weeks paid, gender-neutral parental leave with full superannuation contributions throughout paid and unpaid leave Flexible working arrangements Financial support to obtain work-related professional qualifications Professional membership contributions and generous paid study leave (up to 12 days) Corporate discount available for health insurance, including dependent(s) Employee Assistance Program ("EAP") - free to all employees and their immediate families 35 hours per year for approved pro bono matters Special leave - 2 days per year of a cultural or religious holiday that is not treated as a public holiday in Australia FTI Work Perks: our discount program that provides a wide range of corporate offers, savings, and wellbeing resources Monthly Health & Wellbeing program including fitness subsidies Annual paid volunteer hours Corporate matching for charitable donations Opportunity to join our Reconciliation Action Plan - working group; FTI's Women's Initiative Network (FTI WIN); Diversity, Inclusion & Belonging and Corporate Citizenship committees  About FTIConsulting  What makes us unique? With more than 8,000+ employees located in offices in every corner of the globe, we are the firm our clients call when their most important issues are at stake. Regardless of what level you are, you will have the opportunity to work alongside and learn from top experts in your field on high-profile engagements that impact history. Our culture is collaborative, and we value diversity, recognition, development and making a difference in our communities.  FTI Consulting is publicly traded on the New York Stock Exchange and has been recognised as a Best Firm to Work For by Consulting magazine and one of America's Best Management Consulting Firms by Forbes. For more information, visit www.fticonsulting.com and connect with us on Twitter/X ( @FTIConsulting ), Facebook and LinkedIn.  FTI Consulting is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of race, colour, national origin, ancestry, citizenship status, protected veteran status, religion, physical or mental disability, marital status, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, or any other basis protected by law, ordinance, or regulation.

jobType: We are thrilled to announce a groundbreaking opportunity to join the Sportsbet team - the role of Head of Enterprise AI  This isn't just a new position; it's a new frontier for our company, and we're not just stepping into itwe're leaping with both feet and a jetpack!  Why, you ask? Because embracing Generative AI is like upgrading from a flip phone to the latest smartphone. It's not just about being on the cutting edge; it's about holding the scissors. Generative AI is the powerhouse behind innovations that can write code, create art, and even draft emails funnier than this one (hard to believe, I know).  In an innovative technology company like ours, staying ahead isn't just a goal; it's our mantra. Generative AI is the secret sauce that will help us cook up solutions we haven't even dreamed of yet. It's like having a crystal ball, but instead of vague predictions, it gives us solid prototypes.  Our new Head of Enterprise AI will be the captain of this ship, steering us through the uncharted waters of AI creativity. Genuine flexible working and remote working policy with a $1050 work from home office allowance Development budget to send you to conferences, events, courses and other learning opportunities. Weekly concierge service including free massages, manicure/nail appointments  all onsite! Daily fresh fruit, free breakfast, sparkling water and Kombucha on tap in the office (did we mention we have a Thursday afternoon social hour?) Tailored career development programs with a yearly tools down day to focus on goals End of trip facilities with an onsite table tennis and pool table Access to our employee assistance program and a Circle In membership Were proud of our industry leading Parental Leave support program with 26 weeks paid leave for Primary Carers with no waiting time and two weeks of paid leave for Secondary Carers followed by six weeks unpaid leave. We also have a progressive return to work benefits for your first six months back: come back for three days, get paid for four; come back for four days, get paid for five. Get the Green Tick Feeling - the feeling you get when you Thrive working at Sportsbet!  Whats the Green Tick Feeling?  Well, its different for everyone, yet unites us all. Its the feeling you get when you succeed, no matter what success looks like to you. It could be developing your career, it could be working on an industry leading project, or it could be making it to school pick up in time. It's all the little and big things that make you feel like youre Thriving working at Sportsbet. jobType: Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.  Hey, hello, hiya, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, , hallo, vtejte!  Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you're probably keen to find out what's on offer, so we'll get straight to the point.  Where and how you can work  Our flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. But you have choice in where and how you work. That means if you want to do your thing in the office (if you're near one), at home or a bit of both, it's up to you.  What youd be doing in this role  As Canva scales change continues to be part of our DNA. But we like to think that's all part of the fun. So this will give you the flavour of the type of things you'll be working on when you start, but this will likely evolve.  The Engineering Manager will be coaching two squads of ~4 engineers each, leaning heavily towards backend. They will be managing the team priorities, overseeing goal delivery and collaborating with other team leads. While coding will not be the main focus of this role, there can still be capacity for some hands-on work.  At the moment, this role is focused on:  Leading and coaching a motivated full stack team across two squads of up to 8 engineers and mentoringmembers of the team on technical approaches. Work with senior members of the team to guide the technical vision while being responsible for break-down and delivery of large projects Design, develop and deploy solutions and hands-on software development  working closely with leads, designers, and product managers Foster a impactful and healthy team via a healthy code review culture, knowledge sharing, design showcases, and process improvements Promote a safe and healthy culture with a focus on collaboration and open communication while advocating for engineering needs to non-technical stakeholders within the group Be accountable for the operation of services (including on-call support as part of the team roster, 1 week out of every 4-6 week)  You're probably a match if  Experience leading a team of software engineers building high-performing and collaborative teams. Experience owning and operating services with a healthy balance of delivery leadership, people leadership, and technical skills. Ability to lead by example; promote Canvas values, no-blame mentality, and engineering values. Experience working cross-functionally with Product Managers, Designers, and other business functions outside of engineering. Strong customer focus to understand the use cases and requirements of our internal customers. The requirement, although not he main part of the role, is still to be hands on in our backend tech stack - Java and AWS.   About the team  The public content library is one of the things differentiating Canva from its competition. The role of the Content Platform is to ingest content from external partners and creators, store and serve templates in an efficient way that meets Canvas scale and load and build the admin tools used by our operations team to maintain the state of the library. When it comes to templates, we also play a crucial role in making sure that templates support all the new features and doc types being launched. For example, whiteboards, docs, forms polls & quizzes + much more.  What's in it for you?  Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a stack of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.  Here's a taste of what's on offer:  Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally  Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.  Other stuff to know  We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. title: Delivery Lead
description: The Delivery lead is central to the running of a squad to set them up for success in prioritising, planning and executing on transformation initiat...
jobType: Company Description  Lets create a more sociable future together  At Endeavour, were totally into what we do. With a portfolio that includes Dan Murphys, BWS, ALH Hotels, Pinnacle Drinks and more, we love to bring people together. Together we share our passion for our products and industry; its what inspires us to dream big, and continue to create new experiences for our customers and teams across Australia. If you thrive on positive energy, we want to meet you!  Job Description  Bring your passion and feel the energy Work within an industry leading business during a period of growth Become a key player within transformation inititives  The Delivery leadis central to the running of a squad to set them up for success in prioritising, planning and executing on transformation initiatives using Scrum or Kanban frameworks. They enable the squad through removing any impediments while facilitating transparency of all the work, progress of sprint goals and capacity to interested stakeholders as well as to the squad themselves.  The role is also responsible for ensuring the squad adheres to agile methodologies and principles and involves organising and facilitating agile ceremonies such as daily scrums, backlog refinement, sprint planning and retrospectives.  This role will operate at an operational and strategic level to:  Sound good? Read on.  Here is a taster of what you can expect in this role:  Ensure that agile ceremonies are facilitated effectively (Sprint planning, standups, sizing, retros etc) Responsible for onboarding and uplift of agile values and principles in day-to-day routine Responsible for ensuring full participation of all squad members in the delivery of value Responsible for Continuous Improvement practices and team mindset Responsible for removing squad blockers with support from the Product Manager or management if needed to ensure planned sprints are delivered as expected. Responsible for ensuring team norms are understood and followed Ensures continual improvement practices are applied and agreed actions are implemented Coach the team to be empowered and instill a proactive, positive and innovative team culture Work closely with Product Manager on prioritization of the squad backlog to maximize value delivered Responsible for ongoing health of the squad, ensuring that it is set up to deliver end-to-end outcomes, providing coaching & feedback, ensuring resources are planned effectively and are fully utilized. Ensures that the squad has engaged with business stakeholders (internal customers) insights and feedback during the delivery of their work. A clear link between insights and action development should be visible. Works with other product managers to ensure that their squad backlog is prioritized appropriately to meet cross-team dependencies. Decides whether the work the squad has delivered is ready for release, works with the squad to define criteria for work to be released and is accountable for the quality of the squads released work. Where necessary, support vendor selections as part of the decision to build or buy product solutions.  Qualifications  Now lets talk about you:  Knowledge, understanding and experience of working with Data and/or AI squads Experience working with commercial partners in a complex, matrix organization Experience working in an agile organization or with cross functional teams Demonstrated ability to build collaborative relationships with a diverse range of stakeholders Develops teams that set and deliver to high standards, drive innovation and create value autonomously, while living our culture and values. Strong ability to prioritize, balancing delivery in the short-term while supporting the overall strategy Experience in managing complex dependencies and releases Solid understanding of Agile and Scrum methodology, disciplines and procedures, and ability, to help / guide others on the processes Extensive Experience in Agile delivery - managing product backlogs, prioritizing requests, writing user stories, sprint planning, iterations, retros, stand-ups Eye for detail, and ability to quickly understand requirements and help the team articulate correctly to form the basis for the sprint planning with focus on delivering a quality outcome Experience working and using Agile tools (Jira, Confluence, DevOps) To achieve this role will need strong collaboration with cross functional teams across Endeavour A degree of flexibility will be required in this role as we build and maintain the roadmap.  The benefits are good too!  We offer flexible working in every sense An exclusive discount card for BWS, Dan Murphys, Woolworths, BIG W and other Endeavour Group brands, including our ALH pubs Monthly meeting-free days Your health and wellbeing is your most important asset, and as one of our valued team members, its our first priority. You will have a range of free services to help you live well and support your physical, mental and financial wellbeing Endeavour Group is full of opportunities - use our dedicated learning and development options to grow an idea, yourself, and your career. This is just the start, so dream big.  At Endeavour, we value being a workplace where everyones welcome - if you meet a number of the requirements (and not all), we encourage you to apply.  Additional Information  We are together creators  With a portfolio that includes Dan Murphys, BWS, ALH Hotels, Pinnacle Drinks and more, Endeavour Group is big on sociability. Together we create the moments that bring millions of people together. And together we have more fun, create more opportunities, and score a lot more goals. Were serious about creating a safe, inclusive and fun place to rock up to where equal opportunity is key, and flexibility is part of how we roll.  Were all about creating a more sociable future - for our customers and each other. If this job excites you - and youre close-enough on the requirements, reach out, wed love to hear from you.  You can learn more about working with us on LinkedIn or atendeavourgroupcareers.com.au.  Our Talent Team and Hiring Leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. Endeavour Group is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.  #WeAreTogetherCreators #ComeAsYouAre #DreamBig #FeelTheEnergy #LeaveYourMark #EndeavourGroup

title: Data Business Partner
description: As a Data Business Partner, you'll serve as the expert link between the data team and key business units. Your role involves gaining a thorough und...
jobType: Data Business Partner   Job No.: 538643  Location: Melbourne - CBD & Inner  Job type: Permanent  The role  David Jones exists to inspire like no other and as we continue to deliver on our ambitious transformation agenda in line with our Vision 2025+ strategy, we are committed to creating inspired careers so our people can Thrive.  As a Data Business Partner, you'll serve as the expert link between the data team and key business units. Your role involves gaining a thorough understanding of the data domains relevant to the business areas you support. You'll collaborate closely with stakeholders to identify their data needs, gather requirements, and offer support for dataset analysis as needed.  What does the role involve?  Develop and maintain a comprehensive data dictionary and system audit, detailing the definitions and locations of all domain-related data within the organization. Understand and map the data flows and transformations as domain data moves between internal and external systems. Effectively communicate complex data relationships to business stakeholders in a clear and accessible manner. Serve as the primary point of contact for any data-related questions within the specified domain. Ensure a comprehensive understanding of where all domain data is located, and uphold data privacy, retention, and security policies across all systems within the domain. Contribute to the ongoing development and refinement of data policies and standards. Share domain-specific knowledge and insights with the data team, aiding in the development of best practices and standards. Represent the domain during the selection of new systems. Ensure that new systems comply with established data policies and standards.  Who are we looking for?  Bachelor's or Master's degree in a relevant field such as Data Science, Statistics, Computer Science, or a related discipline. Proven experience as a data analyst, with expertise in data exploration, analysis, and visualization. Domain-specific knowledge and experience in areas relevant to the role (e.g., marketing, finance, supply chain, healthcare, etc.). Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a talent for deriving actionable insights from complex datasets. Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, capable of collaborating effectively with stakeholders at all organizational levels. Keen attention to detail and a dedication to maintaining data quality and accuracy. Ability to work independently and manage multiple priorities in a dynamic, fast-paced environment. Proven experience working in an Agile software delivery environment and experience with a modern data stac  Why work for us?  Unique opportunity to be part of a highly engaged, successful team, focused on the transformation of an iconic Australian brand A competitive remuneration package including performance-based incentives Hybrid working arrangements in office and from home that provide appropriate work/life balance Parental leave policy of 18-weeks paid leave for the primary carer, and 3-weeks paid leave for the supporting partner Generous employee discounts across David Jones and access to partner benefits An additional day of leave for your birthday along with time to support charitable work Opportunities to support community partnerships across our Corporate Social Responsibility program Be a member of a company committed to sustainable practices, driving change in the retail landscape Ongoing training and development to pursue individual ambitions  About Us  Since 1838, David Jones limitless quest for innovation and progress established the brand as Australias original influencer in fashion and lifestyle. Having revolutionised the way Australians shop, David Jones creation of a social centre inspired and created lasting memories for past, present and future generations. Today, our vision to inspire Like No Other drives us to continue this legacy in our ambitious purpose to be the destination that inspires, with experiences and services Like No Other.  Our Thriving cultural pillars inspire our people to deliver on our vision and purpose. We are Customer Obsessed; curious to understand and dedicated to delighting them with seamless solutions as one team. We care for our people, customers, partners and community by creating Inclusive environments through belonging and respect. We Empower with implied trust to act with integrity, value our unique skills and be accountable for our decisions. We constantly seek Innovative ways of improving, changing and exploring ways that we can inspire.  David Jones is an equal opportunity employer committed to providing a working environment that embraces and values diversity and inclusion. If you have any support or access requirements, we encourage you to advise us at time of application to assist you through the recruitment process.  We are a 2024 Circle Back Initiative Employer  we commit to respond to every applicant. If you have any support or access requirements, we encourage you to advise us at time of application to assist you through the recruitment process. Drive the determination of requirements, work with clients including facilitation of workshops, stakeholder interviews other techniques. Translate functional and business requirements into accurate user stories and process flows. Communicate requirement dependencies, issues or risks identified through the analysis process.  Mandatory Skills:  Experience: 4 to 6yrs Required Skills: Technical Skills: ,Agile, Business Analysis & Planning Domain Skills: Online Digital Channel (Web, Mobile)  Roles and Responsibilities:  Technical competencies Significant senior level experience as a lead business analyst in a consultancy/ enterprise context in both Waterfall and Agile environments Substantial experience in the development of User Stories and Agile delivery Extensive experience in facilitation and requirement gathering including workshop facilitation and interview techniques (both Agile or non-Agile) Experience working with software engineers in an enterprise project-based environment based on Agile (i.e. Scrum, Kanban, Lean) General competencies Experience in a consulting position, working within large/ complex and distributed client environments. Our unique industry-based, consultative approach helps clients envision, build and run more innovative and efficient businesses. title: Senior Software Engineer - Developer Platform
description: Riding the wave of technical development at a hyper-growth company offers a unique, once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to do some of the best engineeri...
jobType: Join the team redefining how the world experiences design.  Hey, g'day, mabuhay, kia ora, , hallo, vtejte!  Thanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you're probably keen to find out what's on offer, so we'll get straight to the point.  Where and how you can work  Our flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. But you have choice in where and how you work, we trust our Canvanauts to choose the balance that empowers them and their team to achieve their goals.  What youd be doing in this role  As Canva scales change continues to be part of our DNA. But we like to think that's all part of the fun. So this will give you the flavour of the type of things you'll be working on when you start, but this will likely evolve.  At the moment, this role is focused on:  Developing self-service infrastructure from the ground up to empower our engineering teams to work more efficiently Working across CI, Static Analysis Tooling, IDE Integration (Bazel) and other developer-related domains as necessary to ensure Canvas engineering teams continue to scale with the demands of the product suite Working with product engineering teams to ensure build best practices and tools are rolled out in every service across the whole organization. Designing, building and optimising build frameworks to build and test a monorepo architecture. Participating in solution design meetings, hiring interviews, and code reviews Working to improve/maintain internal developer experience platforms that empower engineers to work efficiently.  You're probably a match if  You have experience building internal tooling for CI, infrastructure, or developer efficiency/productivity You have strong Computer Engineering / Science knowledge around fundamentals and first principles relating to concurrency, multithreading, data structures, architecture, and various design patterns You have advanced coding proficiency in Python/ Java/ GoLang and strong Object Oriented Programming fundamentals You have a good understanding of the DevOps ecosystem concerning tooling, Continuous Delivery, Continuous Integration, Infrastructure as Code You have experience working in a modern distributed microservices environment hosted on AWS You have experience working with infrastructure as code and CI/CD You have the ability to guide and mentor other members within the team and improve the way we collaborate, learn, and share ideas You have strong written and verbal communication skills - both technical and plain language  About the Group  The Developer Platform Group owns the coding life cycle at Canva  from ideas through to production. Our mission is To forge a delightful ecosystem for engineers at Canva, amplifying their craft and enabling them to ship fast and correct. At scale.We create an environment in which developers can do their best work.   We work closely with product engineering teams to understand their needs and build solutions to best meet them. Our ecosystem spans platforms such as Git, build systems, CI systems, and knowledge management systems.   Riding the wave of technical development at a hyper-growth company offers a unique, once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to do some of the best engineering of your life. Tackle complex problems with innovative solutions and enjoy the exhilaration of seeing your contributions amplify developer velocity and workflow at scale. If you crave challenge, love growth and yearn for the satisfaction of seeing real results uplift the developer experience, come and join us in the Developer Platform group.  What's in it for you?  Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a range of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.  Here's a taste of what's on offer:  Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally  Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.  Other stuff to know  We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.  We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva so even if you dont feel like your skills quite match whats listed above - we still want to hear from you!  Please note that interviews are conducted virtually.

Demonstrated experience in day-to-day operations of a hospital environment or an organisation with a similar focus. Solid technical analytical, troubleshooting, and problem-solving skills Experience with tools and technologies such as Cisco Firewall, Network Access Controls, Bluecoat Proxy, Rapid7 - Vulnerability Scan, Cisco ISE, Splunk - Security Information and event Management Availability to perform security operations and support outside of business hours. title: Senior Project Officer
description: Seeking an experienced Senior Project Officer to engage with stakeholders to deliver innovative programs supporting energy efficiency.
jobType: This pay rate is inclusive of mandatory 25% casual loading  Our client is seeking an experienced Senior Project Officer to develop and implement programs and initiatives through engaging with stakeholders and delivery partners, building customer relationships, and administering partnership and delivery agreements and deeds.  You and your team will liaise closely with service providers, decision makers and other key project stakeholders to deliver innovative programs supporting energy efficiency, solar and battery uptake and decarbonisation for Queensland businesses and households.  Initial contract until June 2025| ASAP start Established program of work | Energy sector experience desirable Competitive hourly rate | Flexible work environment (up to 2 days p/week WFH)  What you will do...  Conduct high-level research, interpretation, analysis and review of regulatory and policy issues pertaining to program development/delivery activities. Prepare program material including technical reports, regulatory instruments, briefing material, media and communications, presentations, publications and correspondence. Undertake the development and implementation of program monitoring, analysis, evaluation and reporting to substantiate effective and efficient program governance and appropriate outcomes. Identify program risks and issues and develop and implement mitigation measures to effectively manage these and use sound judgement to escalate as appropriate. Communicate clearly, both verbally and in writing, tailoring messages to suit a variety of audiences. Manage relationships with a wide range of stakeholders at all levels to support the design and delivery of programs. This may include delivery partners, government agencies, stakeholder groups and members of the public. Apply critical thinking, problem-solving and analytical skills to complex matters. Plan, prioritise and manage multiple and competing activities within tight timeframes in a busy work environment as part of a team, or individually. Work flexibly and dynamically within a high performing and cohesive team responsible for delivering government energy programs, policy and initiatives. Embrace change and demonstrate a mindset of innovation and continuous improvement practices to ensure the ongoing development and implementation of enhanced administrative practices and processes Promote an effective working culture by capturing and sharing knowledge and supporting common expectations to develop a sense of collaboration among colleagues.  What you will bring  Experience working in a fast-paced project/program environment. Government experience not necessary, and relevant private sector experience preferred. Prior experience with the energy (or similar) sector desirable, but not essential. Prioritises projects and tasks efficiently, in line with team commitments (Leads strategically) Shares and seeks creative ideas, suggestions and data to inform the delivery of services. High level of skill in operating in a demanding and dynamic work environment and dealing with conflicting priorities to achieve results.  In addition to the above, the client will also consider your ability to  Gain insight into issues by analysing the available information in a critical manner. Share and seeks creative ideas, suggestions and data to inform the delivery of services. Accept decision making responsibility and demonstrates judgement about when to escalate issues. Communicate in a clear, succinct and deliberate manner, adjusting the message so that it resonates with different stakeholders. Demonstrate careful planning and organisation to achieve results. Promote personal responsibility for the realisation of a healthy workplace through regular communication, feedback and sharing of observations and outcomes. Act as a role model for the team by actively seeking feedback and communicating openly about learnings. Analyse information to proactively identify risks to the team's planning activities.  HOW TO APPLY:  Please submit your resume for consideration via the appropriate link. A cover letter demonstrating your relevant experience may also be reviewed.  Should you wish to discuss, please contact Jemma Walker at Jemma.Walker@hudson.com quoting reference number: 239677. Your interest will be treated in the strictest of confidence.

Responsibilities  Provide workforce analytics and reports to executive and senior managers, enabling informed decision-making on workforce-related matters. Manage, coach, and assist in the development of team members to deliver high-quality, efficient, and compliant systems, information, and services. Essential Criteria:  Strong experience in resource and workforce planning frameworks. Background in radio and telecommunications. Demonstrated expertise in project and program management. title: Senior Business Analyst
description: Join Benetas in an exciting opportunity as a Senior Business Analyst and create a meaningful impact supporting projects across the organisation
jobType: Senior Business Analyst  Business improvement & process automation expertise Hawthorn East head office with travel to sites in Victoria Initial 12-month fixed term contract    Aged Care operates in an ever increasing competitive landscape with operational cost pressures, changing consumer needs, and increased focus on service quality, compliance, reporting and operational efficiency. In response, we are investing in a variety of strategic projects to continuously improve how we operate and seek to appoint a Senior Business Analyst to support the Information Technology team to help deliver the IT strategic plan.  For this key transformational IT project, we seek a Senior Business Analyst to start the discovery and service improvement design phase in Residential Aged Care. This will include embedding yourself to analyse the current state of how our 12-homes operate, including their pain points, manual processes, and opportunities to automate information services.  Our objective is to provide knowledge support and minimise administrational overhead for our teams so they can focus on maximising their time and focus on our customers. The challenge will be how you consult with and engage different stakeholders from across the business while maintaining a focus on the objectives of improving operational performance.    Some of the ways youll make a difference:  work with the business units to review operations and services, conduct detailed SWOTS analysis to kick start transformational planning conduct workshops, interviews and other engagement activities model as is business processes, perform gap analysis to identify opportunities and define how enabling technology can maximise delivery outcomes develop future state operating model options, maximizing the use and value of information automation and process rationalisation, re-engineering of business processes and systems to simplify human knowledge support and service administration communicate risks and benefits of the future state design generate cost-benefit assessments for transformation options to guide project direction from an evidence base review engage with stakeholders to agree on future state models create relevant future state and transition models using appropriate techniques for sponsored solutions.    To help you achieve this, you will be:  a capable observer and listener to embed yourself in, and develop a deep understanding of the business, challenges and opportunities in this growing sector curious but also able to questions why to determine evidence based solutions able to translate and quantify benefits (cost savings, activity automation, performance improvements) experienced in business assessment, gap analysis, process engineering, reengineering, process and service overhauling articulate and able to develop consultative stakeholder relationships able to translate technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders able to use a suite of tools to develop and document requirements and solutions design (process mapping, data modelling, data flow modelling, ER modelling) experienced with complex projects that involve taking stakeholders on a journey to improve operational outcomes tertiary qualified in a related degree (Information Technology) and related certifications (i.e. Agile, Six Sigma etc)    Why work with us?  Work with a passionate, talented IT team and business teams with a great empathy, supportive and collaborative culture Partner with our business stakeholders to really make a difference in how we operate Close to public transport with nearby parking options in Toorak Road, Hawthorn East Not-for-profit salary packaging up to $18,300 per year - offering you more take home pay with less tax! Work on highly diverse and exciting projects Proudly being part of a business that values Respect, Responsibility, Community, and Spirit    Interested in applying:  We are proud to provide an inclusive workplace - with a diverse workforce that reflects the client base .We respect and value differences and encourage people of all ages backgrounds to apply. Please note we may consider applications on an ongoing basis and therefore encourage you to apply at your earliest opportunity. The successful candidate will need to undertake a police check andprovide proof of immunisation for the current annual flu immunisation.    What do we do? We care  in a big way!  We make a difference - We have been caring for older Victorians for over 70 years, providing a safe and supportive services that cater for all such asresidential aged care, retirement living, respite, primary care and in-home services  all across Victoria.  By working with our values in mind  Respect, Responsibility, Community, and Spirit, we are able to care for and celebrate every client and resident for being the incredible individual that they are. Not only do we celebrate our residents, but we celebrate each other.  Have a meaningful career with Benetas where the work that you do will really matter. Should you apply? It is a yes from us!
